1
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:53,820
I believe in America.

2
00:00:54,190 --> 00:00:56,690
America has made my fortune

3
00:00:57,293 --> 00:00:59,793
and I raised my daughter
in the American fashion.

4
00:01:01,464 --> 00:01:04,228
I gave her freedom,
but I taught her

5
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:06,833
never to dishonor her family.

6
00:01:07,703 --> 00:01:10,934
She found a boyfriend.
Not an Italian.

7
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:13,375
She went to the movies with him.

8
00:01:13,376 --> 00:01:16,470
She stayed out late.
I didn't protest.

9
00:01:18,247 --> 00:01:21,080
Two months ago,
he took her for a drive

10
00:01:21,183 --> 00:01:23,683
with another boyfriend.

11
00:01:24,020 --> 00:01:26,648
They made her drink whiskey,

12
00:01:26,756 --> 00:01:29,953
and then they tried
to take advantage of her.

13
00:01:31,193 --> 00:01:33,361
She resisted.

14
00:01:33,362 --> 00:01:35,862
She kept her honor.

15
00:01:36,599 --> 00:01:39,625
So they beat her like an animal.

16
00:01:41,571 --> 00:01:45,268
When I went to the hospital,
her nose was broken...

17
00:01:46,576 --> 00:01:48,710
her jaw was shattered...

18
00:01:48,711 --> 00:01:51,211
held together by wire.

19
00:01:53,249 --> 00:01:55,809
She couldn't even weep
because of the pain.

20
00:01:58,654 --> 00:02:02,146
But I wept.
Why did I weep?

21
00:02:04,827 --> 00:02:07,327
She was the light of my life.

22
00:02:09,198 --> 00:02:11,698
Beautiful girl.

23
00:02:14,670 --> 00:02:17,170
Now she will never
be beautiful again.

24
00:02:24,313 --> 00:02:26,813
Sorry.

25
00:02:34,957 --> 00:02:37,457
I, I went to the police,
like a good American.

26
00:02:38,527 --> 00:02:41,027
These two boys
were brought to trial.

27
00:02:42,331 --> 00:02:45,095
A judge sentence them
to three years in prison...

28
00:02:45,201 --> 00:02:47,701
and suspend their sentence.

29
00:02:48,504 --> 00:02:51,004
Suspended the sentence.

30
00:02:51,073 --> 00:02:53,573
They went free that very day.

31
00:02:55,745 --> 00:02:58,245
I stood in the courtroom
like a fool.

32
00:02:59,115 --> 00:03:02,380
And those two bastard,
they smiled at me.

33
00:03:03,953 --> 00:03:07,389
Then I said to my wife,
"For justice...

34
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:09,990
we must go to Don Corleone."

35
00:03:14,897 --> 00:03:18,196
Why did you go to the police?
Why didn't you come to me first?

36
00:03:19,368 --> 00:03:21,202
What do you want of me?

37
00:03:21,203 --> 00:03:24,297
Tell me anything,
but do what I beg you to do.

38
00:03:25,508 --> 00:03:28,008
What is that?

39
00:03:51,901 --> 00:03:54,401
That I cannot do.

40
00:03:54,904 --> 00:03:57,404
I'll give you anything you ask.

41
00:03:59,809 --> 00:04:02,573
We've known each other many years,
but this is the first time...

42
00:04:02,678 --> 00:04:06,011
you ever came to me
for counsel or for help.

43
00:04:06,115 --> 00:04:09,050
I can't remember the last time
that you invited me...

44
00:04:09,151 --> 00:04:11,651
to your house
for a cup of coffee...

45
00:04:12,722 --> 00:04:16,385
even though my wife
is godmother to your only child.

46
00:04:16,492 --> 00:04:18,760
But let's be frank.

47
00:04:18,761 --> 00:04:21,261
You never wanted my friendship...

48
00:04:21,764 --> 00:04:25,393
and you were afraid
to be in my debt.

49
00:04:25,501 --> 00:04:28,001
I didn't want
to get into trouble.

50
00:04:29,105 --> 00:04:31,605
I understand.

51
00:04:32,007 --> 00:04:34,507
You found paradise in America.

52
00:04:37,313 --> 00:04:39,314
You had a good trade,
you made a good living.

53
00:04:39,315 --> 00:04:42,011
Police protected you,
and there were courts of law.

54
00:04:42,118 --> 00:04:44,618
So you didn't need
a friend like me.

55
00:04:46,455 --> 00:04:50,016
But, now you come to me
and you say,

56
00:04:50,126 --> 00:04:52,626
"Don Corleone, give me justice."

57
00:04:54,363 --> 00:04:57,230
But you don't ask with respect.

58
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:59,893
You don't offer friendship.

59
00:05:00,002 --> 00:05:02,502
You don't even think
to call me 'Godfather.'

60
00:05:03,672 --> 00:05:05,440
Instead, you come into my house

61
00:05:05,441 --> 00:05:07,442
on the day my daughter
is to be married

62
00:05:07,443 --> 00:05:09,943
and you ask me to do murder
for money.

63
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:13,340
I ask you for justice.

64
00:05:13,449 --> 00:05:16,179
That is not justice.
Your daughter is still alive.

65
00:05:17,486 --> 00:05:20,853
They must suffer then
as she suffers.

66
00:05:22,925 --> 00:05:25,425
How much shall I pay you?

67
00:05:39,975 --> 00:05:42,475
Bonasera. Bonasera.

68
00:05:44,013 --> 00:05:47,380
What have I ever done to make you
treat me so disrespectfully?

69
00:05:49,185 --> 00:05:51,745
If you'd come to me
in friendship,

70
00:05:51,854 --> 00:05:53,855
then the scum
that ruined your daughter

71
00:05:53,856 --> 00:05:56,356
would be suffering
this very day.

72
00:05:57,326 --> 00:05:58,593
And if, by chance,

73
00:05:58,594 --> 00:06:00,662
an honest man like yourself
should make enemies,

74
00:06:00,663 --> 00:06:03,163
then they would become
my enemies.

75
00:06:05,267 --> 00:06:07,767
And then they would fear you.

76
00:06:11,841 --> 00:06:14,341
Be my friend?

77
00:06:17,780 --> 00:06:20,280
Godfather.

78
00:06:23,853 --> 00:06:26,353
Good.

79
00:06:27,022 --> 00:06:29,390
Someday, and that day
may never come...

80
00:06:29,391 --> 00:06:31,891
I'll call upon you
to do a service for me.

81
00:06:33,696 --> 00:06:36,196
But until that day...

82
00:06:37,466 --> 00:06:40,458
accept this justice as a gift
on my daughter's wedding day.

83
00:06:41,937 --> 00:06:44,437
<i>- Grazie, Godfather.
- Prego</i>

84
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,980
Give this to Clemenza.

85
00:06:56,485 --> 00:06:57,919
I want reliable people,

86
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,121
people that aren't
going to be carried away.

87
00:07:00,122 --> 00:07:01,656
I mean, we're not murderers,

88
00:07:01,657 --> 00:07:04,217
in spite of what
this undertaker says.

89
00:07:29,551 --> 00:07:31,219
- Where's Michael?
- What? Don't worry.

90
00:07:31,220 --> 00:07:32,987
It's early. He'll be here.

91
00:07:32,988 --> 00:07:34,222
We're not taking it.

92
00:07:34,223 --> 00:07:36,723
We're not taking the picture
without Michael.

93
00:07:37,224 --> 00:07:39,224
<i>No picture now.</i>

94
00:07:43,098 --> 00:07:45,598
- What's the matter, Sonny?
- It's Michael.

95
00:08:35,617 --> 00:08:38,117
Don Barzini.

96
00:08:40,618 --> 00:08:42,618
<i>Welcome to our house.</i>

97
00:08:53,836 --> 00:08:56,964
Hey, Paulie!
Let me have some wine.

98
00:08:57,072 --> 00:08:59,632
Paulie! More wine.

99
00:08:59,742 --> 00:09:01,009
<i>Scusi, please.</i>

100
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:02,844
You look terrif on the floor.

101
00:09:02,845 --> 00:09:05,345
What are you,
a dance judge or something?

102
00:09:06,348 --> 00:09:08,848
Go take a walk around
the neighborhood. Do your job.

103
00:09:16,392 --> 00:09:18,393
Hey, Sandra, come on. Do me a favor.
Watch the kids.

104
00:09:18,394 --> 00:09:21,354
- Don't let 'em run wild, all right?
- Well, you watch yourself, all right?

105
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:45,820
Twenty or thirty grand.

106
00:09:45,821 --> 00:09:48,321
In small bills, cash.

107
00:09:48,657 --> 00:09:51,157
In that little silk purse.

108
00:09:51,593 --> 00:09:54,093
If this was
somebody else's wedding.

109
00:09:54,763 --> 00:09:57,561
<i>Hey, Paulie!
I got two gobbagool...</i>

110
00:09:57,666 --> 00:09:59,534
<i>gabagol and a prosciutto.</i>

111
00:09:59,535 --> 00:10:02,035
Stupid jerk!

112
00:10:10,245 --> 00:10:12,745
Hey, what's the matter?

113
00:10:24,326 --> 00:10:26,727
- I have to go back to work.
- Oh, Tom.

114
00:10:26,728 --> 00:10:28,062
It's part of the wedding.

115
00:10:28,063 --> 00:10:30,964
No Sicilian can refuse any request
on his daughter's wedding day.

116
00:10:37,005 --> 00:10:39,340
Don Corleone,
I am honored and grateful...

117
00:10:39,341 --> 00:10:41,841
that you have invited me
to your home...

118
00:10:46,515 --> 00:10:47,715
Get outta here.

119
00:10:47,716 --> 00:10:50,216
This is a private party.
Go on.

120
00:10:51,153 --> 00:10:53,653
What is it?
Hey, my sister's wedding.

121
00:11:00,729 --> 00:11:03,229
Goddamn FBI
don't respect nothin'.

122
00:11:05,901 --> 00:11:09,200
Hey, come here, come here.
Come here!

123
00:11:10,572 --> 00:11:13,072
There.

124
00:11:23,986 --> 00:11:26,087
But towards the end
he was paroled...

125
00:11:26,088 --> 00:11:28,716
to help with
the American war effort.

126
00:11:28,824 --> 00:11:31,324
For the last six months, he's been
working at my pastry shop.

127
00:11:31,927 --> 00:11:34,095
Nazorine, my friend,
what can I do for you?

128
00:11:34,096 --> 00:11:36,596
Now that the war is over...

129
00:11:36,665 --> 00:11:39,725
this boy, Enzo, they want
to repatriate him back to Italy.

130
00:11:40,836 --> 00:11:43,396
Godfather, I have a daughter.

131
00:11:43,505 --> 00:11:46,005
See, she and Enzo...

132
00:11:46,942 --> 00:11:49,010
You want Enzo to stay
in this country...

133
00:11:49,011 --> 00:11:51,511
and you want your daughter
to be married.

134
00:11:52,581 --> 00:11:55,081
You understand everything.

135
00:11:55,784 --> 00:11:58,284
Mr. Hagen. Thank you.

136
00:12:00,856 --> 00:12:02,857
And wait till you see
the beautiful wedding cake...

137
00:12:02,858 --> 00:12:04,292
I made for your daughter.

138
00:12:04,293 --> 00:12:06,853
Like this, with the bride
and the groom and...

139
00:12:13,135 --> 00:12:16,195
- Who should I give this job to?
- Not to our paisan.

140
00:12:17,906 --> 00:12:20,500
Give it to a Jew congressman
in another district.

141
00:12:21,643 --> 00:12:24,143
Who else is on the list?

142
00:12:30,285 --> 00:12:32,486
Hey, Michael.
How are you?

143
00:12:32,487 --> 00:12:34,987
Hello.

144
00:12:51,673 --> 00:12:54,403
He's not on the list,
but Luca Brasi wants to see you.

145
00:13:00,849 --> 00:13:03,184
Is this... Is this necessary?

146
00:13:03,185 --> 00:13:05,119
He didn't expect to be invited
to the wedding...

147
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,188
so he wanted to thank you.

148
00:13:07,189 --> 00:13:08,889
All right.

149
00:13:08,890 --> 00:13:12,121
Don Corleone,
I am honored and grateful...

150
00:13:12,227 --> 00:13:14,727
that you have invited me
to your home...

151
00:13:14,830 --> 00:13:17,330
on the wedding day
of your daughter.

152
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:20,233
And may their first child
be a masculine child.

153
00:13:20,335 --> 00:13:22,860
- Don...
- Michael?

154
00:13:22,971 --> 00:13:24,538
Don Corleone...

155
00:13:24,539 --> 00:13:27,039
That man over there
is talking to himself.

156
00:13:27,943 --> 00:13:30,443
See that scary guy over there?

157
00:13:30,979 --> 00:13:32,280
He's a very scary guy.

158
00:13:32,281 --> 00:13:34,615
Who is he?
What's his name?

159
00:13:34,616 --> 00:13:37,210
His name is Luca Brasi...

160
00:13:37,319 --> 00:13:39,819
and he helps my father out
sometimes.

161
00:13:40,422 --> 00:13:43,118
Oh, Michael, wait a minute.
He's coming over here.

162
00:13:43,119 --> 00:13:44,119
Mike!

163
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,620
Ho! Tom.

164
00:13:45,621 --> 00:13:47,121
Heyyy!

165
00:13:48,297 --> 00:13:50,197
You look terrific!

166
00:13:50,198 --> 00:13:52,400
My brother Tom Hagen.
This is Kay Adams.

167
00:13:52,401 --> 00:13:54,926
- How do you do?
- Nice to meet you.

168
00:13:55,037 --> 00:13:57,405
Your father's
been asking for you.

169
00:13:57,406 --> 00:13:59,140
- Very nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

170
00:13:59,141 --> 00:14:01,641
I'll be there.

171
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:04,706
If he's your brother,
why does he have a different name?

172
00:14:05,814 --> 00:14:07,815
Oh, uh, when my brother Sonny was a kid...

173
00:14:07,816 --> 00:14:10,316
he found Tom Hagen in the street,
and he had no home.

174
00:14:11,219 --> 00:14:13,719
And so my father took him in...

175
00:14:14,289 --> 00:14:16,789
and he's been with us ever since.

176
00:14:17,492 --> 00:14:19,992
He's a good lawyer.

177
00:14:20,429 --> 00:14:22,797
Not a Sicilian, but...

178
00:14:22,798 --> 00:14:25,132
I think he's gonna be consigliere.

179
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:27,633
- What's that?
- That's...

180
00:14:28,203 --> 00:14:29,904
like a counselor, an advisor.

181
00:14:29,905 --> 00:14:32,405
Very important to the family.

182
00:14:32,974 --> 00:14:35,474
You like your lasagna?

183
00:14:39,448 --> 00:14:44,385
Don Corleone,
I am honored and grateful...

184
00:14:44,486 --> 00:14:47,717
that you have invited me
to your daughter's wedding...

185
00:14:53,328 --> 00:14:55,828
on the day
of your daughter's wedding.

186
00:14:56,765 --> 00:14:59,598
And I hope
that their first child...

187
00:14:59,701 --> 00:15:02,201
be a masculine child.

188
00:15:03,038 --> 00:15:08,066
I pledge my ever-ending loyalty.

189
00:15:09,945 --> 00:15:11,946
For your daughter's
bridal purse.

190
00:15:11,947 --> 00:15:14,939
Thank you, Luca,
my most valued friend.

191
00:15:15,050 --> 00:15:18,508
Don Corleone,
I'm gonna leave you now...

192
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,688
because I know you are busy.

193
00:15:20,689 --> 00:15:23,189
Thank you.

194
00:17:26,915 --> 00:17:29,679
Senator Cauly apologized
for not coming personally...

195
00:17:29,784 --> 00:17:32,284
but said you'd understand.

196
00:17:32,621 --> 00:17:35,121
Also some of the judges.

197
00:17:35,624 --> 00:17:38,124
They've all sent gifts.

198
00:17:39,961 --> 00:17:42,461
What is that outside?

199
00:17:50,438 --> 00:17:53,100
Johnny!

200
00:17:56,044 --> 00:17:58,544
I love you.

201
00:18:04,619 --> 00:18:07,247
Hey, Johnny, look over here!

202
00:18:07,355 --> 00:18:10,085
He came all the way from California
to come to the wedding.

203
00:18:10,191 --> 00:18:12,293
- I told you he was going to come.
- It's been two years.

204
00:18:12,294 --> 00:18:14,794
- He's probably in trouble again.
- He's a good godson.

205
00:18:19,034 --> 00:18:21,534
Sing a song.

206
00:18:35,717 --> 00:18:38,584
Michael, you never told me
you knew Johnny Fontane.

207
00:18:38,687 --> 00:18:42,646
- Sure. You wanna meet him?
- Huh? Oh, well, sure.

208
00:18:42,757 --> 00:18:44,825
My father helped him
with his career.

209
00:18:44,826 --> 00:18:47,920
- For my Connie.
- He did? How?

210
00:18:48,029 --> 00:18:49,797
<i>I have but one</i>

211
00:18:49,798 --> 00:18:51,732
- Let's listen to the song.
- No, Michael

212
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,367
<i>Heart</i>

213
00:18:53,368 --> 00:18:57,065
<i>This heart I bring you</i>

214
00:18:58,673 --> 00:19:03,007
<i>I have but one heart</i>

215
00:19:03,111 --> 00:19:05,611
<i>To share with you</i>

216
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:12,349
<i>I have but one dream</i>

217
00:19:12,454 --> 00:19:16,049
<i>That I can cling to</i>

218
00:19:17,525 --> 00:19:22,224
<i>You are the one dream</i>

219
00:19:22,330 --> 00:19:25,595
<i>I pray comes true</i>

220
00:19:26,534 --> 00:19:28,736
Please, Michael. Tell me.

221
00:19:28,737 --> 00:19:32,400
<i>My darling, until I saw you</i>

222
00:19:32,507 --> 00:19:34,508
Well, when Johnny was first starting out...

223
00:19:34,509 --> 00:19:37,376
he was signed to this
personal service contract...

224
00:19:37,479 --> 00:19:39,979
with a big bandleader.

225
00:19:40,415 --> 00:19:42,483
And as his career
got better and better...

226
00:19:42,484 --> 00:19:44,984
he wanted to get out of it.

227
00:19:45,687 --> 00:19:48,383
Now, Johnny is
my father's godson...

228
00:19:48,490 --> 00:19:50,990
and my father went
to see this bandleader...

229
00:19:51,926 --> 00:19:54,426
and he offered him
$10,000 to let Johnny go.

230
00:19:55,897 --> 00:19:58,397
But the bandleader said no.

231
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:01,860
So the next day
my father went to see him...

232
00:20:01,970 --> 00:20:04,470
only this time with Luca Brasi.

233
00:20:06,107 --> 00:20:09,201
And within an hour,
he signed a release...

234
00:20:11,346 --> 00:20:13,974
for a certified check of $1,000.

235
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:16,850
How'd he do that?

236
00:20:16,851 --> 00:20:19,376
My father made him an offer
he couldn't refuse.

237
00:20:20,822 --> 00:20:23,322
What was that?

238
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:26,154
Luca Brasi
held a gun to his head...

239
00:20:26,261 --> 00:20:28,529
and my father assured him
that either his brains...

240
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:31,030
or his signature
would be on the contract.

241
00:20:36,604 --> 00:20:39,104
That's a true story.

242
00:20:49,484 --> 00:20:51,984
That's my family, Kay.
It's not me.

243
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,333
Beautiful!

244
00:21:15,276 --> 00:21:17,644
My godson comes all the way
from California.

245
00:21:17,645 --> 00:21:20,145
Give him a glass of wine.

246
00:21:38,867 --> 00:21:41,367
I'll take care of it.

247
00:21:42,937 --> 00:21:45,838
I want you to find Santino.
Tell him to come to the office.

248
00:21:53,882 --> 00:21:56,382
How are you, Fredo?

249
00:21:57,018 --> 00:21:59,518
My brother Fredo.
This is Kay Adams.

250
00:22:00,622 --> 00:22:03,122
- Hi.
- How ya doin'?

251
00:22:04,893 --> 00:22:08,090
- This is my brother Mike.
- Are you having a good time?

252
00:22:08,196 --> 00:22:10,696
Yeah.
This is your friend, huh?

253
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:16,097
I don't know what to do.
My voice is, is weak.

254
00:22:16,204 --> 00:22:18,539
It's weak.

255
00:22:18,540 --> 00:22:21,168
Anyway, if I had this part
in the picture, you know...

256
00:22:21,276 --> 00:22:23,904
it puts me right back
up on top again.

257
00:22:25,013 --> 00:22:27,513
But this, uh...

258
00:22:27,682 --> 00:22:29,783
this man out there,
he won't give it to me.

259
00:22:29,784 --> 00:22:31,852
- The head of the studio.
- What's his name?

260
00:22:31,853 --> 00:22:34,447
Woltz. Woltz.
He won't give it to me...

261
00:22:34,556 --> 00:22:38,117
and he says
there's no chance, no chance.

262
00:22:42,130 --> 00:22:44,630
Sonny?

263
00:22:45,331 --> 00:22:46,331
Sonny?

264
00:22:52,873 --> 00:22:53,873
Sonny?

265
00:22:54,774 --> 00:22:56,602
Sonny, you in there?

266
00:22:56,844 --> 00:22:59,344
- What?
- The old man wants to see you.

267
00:23:00,815 --> 00:23:03,315
All right, one minute.

268
00:23:17,031 --> 00:23:20,057
A month ago, he bought
the movie rights to this book.

269
00:23:20,168 --> 00:23:22,002
A best-seller.

270
00:23:22,003 --> 00:23:24,304
And the main character
is a guy just like me.

271
00:23:24,305 --> 00:23:26,805
Why, I wouldn't even
have to act.

272
00:23:26,908 --> 00:23:28,308
Just be myself.

273
00:23:28,309 --> 00:23:32,177
Oh, Godfather, I don't know what to do.
I don't know what to do.

274
00:23:33,548 --> 00:23:36,517
You can act like a man!
What's the matter with you?

275
00:23:37,852 --> 00:23:39,353
Is this how you turned out?

276
00:23:39,354 --> 00:23:41,982
A Hollywood finocchio
that cries like a woman?

277
00:23:43,658 --> 00:23:45,993
"What can I do?"
"What can I do?"

278
00:23:45,994 --> 00:23:47,561
What is that nonsense?

279
00:23:47,562 --> 00:23:50,062
Ridiculous!

280
00:23:54,035 --> 00:23:57,334
- You spend time with your family?
- Sure I do.

281
00:23:57,438 --> 00:23:59,006
Good.

282
00:23:59,007 --> 00:24:01,108
Because the man who doesn't
spend time with his family...

283
00:24:01,109 --> 00:24:03,443
can never be a real man.

284
00:24:03,444 --> 00:24:05,944
Come here.

285
00:24:09,417 --> 00:24:11,917
You look terrible.
I want you to eat.

286
00:24:13,021 --> 00:24:15,155
I want you to rest well,
and a month from now...

287
00:24:15,156 --> 00:24:18,284
this Hollywood big shot's
gonna give you what you want.

288
00:24:18,393 --> 00:24:20,893
Too late.
They start shooting in a week.

289
00:24:21,663 --> 00:24:24,163
I'm gonna make him an offer
he can't refuse.

290
00:24:27,602 --> 00:24:29,670
Now just go outside,
enjoy yourself and...

291
00:24:29,671 --> 00:24:32,265
forget about all this nonsense.

292
00:24:33,775 --> 00:24:36,369
Listen. I want you
to leave it all to me.

293
00:24:37,312 --> 00:24:39,812
All right.

294
00:25:03,037 --> 00:25:05,801
What time does my daughter
leave with the bridegroom?

295
00:25:05,907 --> 00:25:08,407
In a few minutes,
right after they cut the cake.

296
00:25:08,409 --> 00:25:11,606
Now, your new son-in-law,
we give him something important.

297
00:25:11,713 --> 00:25:14,081
Never.
Give him a living...

298
00:25:14,082 --> 00:25:17,108
but never discuss
the family business with him.

299
00:25:17,218 --> 00:25:18,618
What else?

300
00:25:18,619 --> 00:25:20,220
Virgil Sollozzo called.

301
00:25:20,221 --> 00:25:22,622
We have to give him a day
sometime next week.

302
00:25:22,623 --> 00:25:25,123
We'll discuss him when you
come back from California.

303
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,494
When am I going to California?

304
00:25:27,495 --> 00:25:29,596
I want you to go tonight.

305
00:25:29,597 --> 00:25:32,395
I want you to talk
to this movie big shot...

306
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:35,000
and settle this business
for Johnny.

307
00:25:36,037 --> 00:25:38,938
Now if there's nothing else, I'd like
to go to my daughter's wedding.

308
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:44,810
Carlo, we're gonna take
the picture.

309
00:25:46,447 --> 00:25:48,281
Wait a minute.

310
00:25:48,282 --> 00:25:50,782
No, Michael, not me.

311
00:25:53,688 --> 00:25:55,022
Just a little closer.

312
00:25:55,023 --> 00:25:57,523
Okay, that's it.
Just like that now. Hold it.

313
00:27:42,363 --> 00:27:44,863
Isn't that nice?

314
00:27:49,837 --> 00:27:51,571
All right, start talking.

315
00:27:51,572 --> 00:27:54,072
I was sent by a friend
of Johnny Fontane.

316
00:27:54,876 --> 00:27:57,538
This friend is my client and would
give his undying friendship...

317
00:27:57,645 --> 00:28:01,376
to Mr. Woltz, if Mr. Woltz
would grant us a small favor.

318
00:28:01,482 --> 00:28:03,982
Woltz is listening.

319
00:28:03,985 --> 00:28:07,079
Give Johnny the part in that new
war film you're starting next week.

320
00:28:13,761 --> 00:28:16,753
And what favor
would your friend...

321
00:28:16,864 --> 00:28:18,765
grant Mr. Woltz?

322
00:28:18,766 --> 00:28:20,667
You're gonna have
some union problems.

323
00:28:20,668 --> 00:28:22,502
My client could make them disappear.

324
00:28:22,503 --> 00:28:24,638
Also, one of your top stars
has just moved...

325
00:28:24,639 --> 00:28:26,640
from marijuana to heroin.

326
00:28:26,641 --> 00:28:28,642
- Are you trying to muscle me?
- Absolutely not.

327
00:28:28,643 --> 00:28:31,044
Now listen to me,
you smooth-talking son of a bitch!

328
00:28:31,045 --> 00:28:33,707
Let me lay it on the line for you
and your boss, whoever he is!

329
00:28:33,814 --> 00:28:35,448
Johnny Fontane
will never get that movie.

330
00:28:35,449 --> 00:28:37,949
I don't care
how many dago, guinea, wop...

331
00:28:37,952 --> 00:28:40,320
greaseball goombahs
come outta the woodwork.

332
00:28:40,321 --> 00:28:41,588
I'm German-Irish.

333
00:28:41,589 --> 00:28:44,183
Well, let me tell you something,
my kraut mick friend.

334
00:28:44,292 --> 00:28:47,193
I'm going to make so much trouble for you,
you won't know what hit you.

335
00:28:47,295 --> 00:28:49,296
Mr. Woltz, I'm a lawyer.
I have not threatened...

336
00:28:49,297 --> 00:28:52,198
I know almost every big lawyer
in New York. Who the hell are you?

337
00:28:52,300 --> 00:28:55,531
I have a special practice.
I handle one client.

338
00:28:55,636 --> 00:28:58,136
Now, you have my number.
I'll wait for your call.

339
00:28:59,540 --> 00:29:02,040
By the way, I admire
your pictures very much.

340
00:29:06,981 --> 00:29:09,481
Check him out.

341
00:29:31,305 --> 00:29:33,805
- This is really beautiful.
- Look at this.

342
00:29:33,908 --> 00:29:36,109
It used to decorate
the palace of a king.

343
00:29:36,110 --> 00:29:38,411
Oh, yeah. Very nice.

344
00:29:38,412 --> 00:29:41,040
Why didn't you say
you worked for Corleone, Tom?

345
00:29:41,148 --> 00:29:43,416
I thought you were just
some cheap, two-bit hustler...

346
00:29:43,417 --> 00:29:45,485
Johnny was running in,
trying to bluff me.

347
00:29:45,486 --> 00:29:47,986
I don't like to use his name
unless it's really necessary.

348
00:29:47,989 --> 00:29:49,589
- How's your drink, Tom?
- Fine.

349
00:29:49,590 --> 00:29:52,320
Hey, come on over here with me. I want to
show you something really beautiful.

350
00:29:52,426 --> 00:29:54,926
You do appreciate beauty,
don't you, Tom?

351
00:29:57,965 --> 00:30:00,991
There you are.
$600,000 on four hooves.

352
00:30:01,102 --> 00:30:02,435
I'll bet Russian czars...

353
00:30:02,436 --> 00:30:04,771
never paid that kind of dough
for a single horse.

354
00:30:04,772 --> 00:30:07,272
Khartoum.

355
00:30:10,144 --> 00:30:14,103
I'm not gonna race him, though.
I'm gonna put him out to stud.

356
00:30:14,215 --> 00:30:15,782
Beautiful.

357
00:30:15,783 --> 00:30:17,450
- Thanks, Tony.
- You're welcome.

358
00:30:17,451 --> 00:30:19,951
- Come on.
- Let's get something to eat.

359
00:30:21,422 --> 00:30:23,922
Mr. Corleone
is Johnny's godfather.

360
00:30:24,892 --> 00:30:27,260
To the Italian people,
that's a very religious...

361
00:30:27,261 --> 00:30:29,262
sacred, close relationship.

362
00:30:29,263 --> 00:30:30,397
I respect that.

363
00:30:30,398 --> 00:30:32,898
Just tell him he should ask me
anything else.

364
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,500
But this is one favor
I can't give him.

365
00:30:35,803 --> 00:30:38,303
He never asks a second favor
when he's been refused the first.

366
00:30:38,372 --> 00:30:41,364
- Understood?
- You don't understand.

367
00:30:41,475 --> 00:30:43,975
Johnny Fontane
never gets that movie.

368
00:30:45,413 --> 00:30:49,076
That part is perfect for him.
It'll make him a big star.

369
00:30:49,183 --> 00:30:51,184
I'm gonna run him
out of the business.

370
00:30:51,185 --> 00:30:53,685
And let me tell you why.

371
00:30:55,389 --> 00:30:58,051
Johnny Fontane ruined
one of Woltz International's...

372
00:30:58,159 --> 00:31:00,160
most valuable protégés.

373
00:31:00,161 --> 00:31:02,495
For five years,
we had her under training.

374
00:31:02,496 --> 00:31:05,556
Singing lessons,
acting lessons, dancing lessons.

375
00:31:05,666 --> 00:31:08,068
I spent hundreds of thousands
of dollars on her.

376
00:31:08,069 --> 00:31:10,370
I was gonna make her a big star.

377
00:31:10,371 --> 00:31:13,101
And let me be even more frank.

378
00:31:13,207 --> 00:31:15,608
Just to show you that I'm not
a hard-hearted man...

379
00:31:15,609 --> 00:31:18,134
that it's not all dollars and cents.

380
00:31:18,245 --> 00:31:20,045
She was beautiful!

381
00:31:20,275 --> 00:31:22,275
She was young, she was innocent!

382
00:31:22,282 --> 00:31:24,284
She was the greatest piece of ass
I've ever had...

383
00:31:24,285 --> 00:31:26,785
and I've had 'em all over the world!

384
00:31:27,488 --> 00:31:29,656
And then Johnny Fontane comes along...

385
00:31:29,657 --> 00:31:32,558
with his olive oil voice and guinea charm.

386
00:31:33,861 --> 00:31:36,361
And she runs off.

387
00:31:36,731 --> 00:31:39,723
She threw it all away
just to make me look ridiculous...

388
00:31:40,935 --> 00:31:43,370
and a man in my position can't afford...

389
00:31:43,371 --> 00:31:46,135
to be made to look ridiculous!

390
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:48,641
Now you get the hell outta here!

391
00:31:48,642 --> 00:31:50,777
And if that goombah
tries any rough stuff...

392
00:31:50,778 --> 00:31:53,278
you tell him I ain't no bandleader.

393
00:31:54,548 --> 00:31:57,176
Yeah. I heard that story.

394
00:31:58,285 --> 00:32:00,785
Thank you for the dinner
and a very pleasant evening.

395
00:32:02,223 --> 00:32:04,817
If your car could take me
to the airport...

396
00:32:04,925 --> 00:32:08,725
Mr. Corleone is a man who insists
on hearing bad news immediately.

397
00:34:01,675 --> 00:34:05,372
- You're not too tired are you, Tom?
- No, I slept on the plane.

398
00:34:05,479 --> 00:34:07,979
I have the Sollozzo notes here.

399
00:34:08,616 --> 00:34:11,116
Now...

400
00:34:11,919 --> 00:34:14,419
Sollozzo is known as "The Turk."

401
00:34:15,389 --> 00:34:17,457
He's supposed to be
very good with a knife...

402
00:34:17,458 --> 00:34:19,259
<i>but only
in matters of business...</i>

403
00:34:19,260 --> 00:34:21,760
<i>with some sort
of reasonable complaint.</i>

404
00:34:22,530 --> 00:34:25,090
<i>His business is narcotics.</i>

405
00:34:25,199 --> 00:34:28,532
<i>He has fields in Turkey
where they grow the poppy...</i>

406
00:34:28,636 --> 00:34:31,537
<i>and in Sicily he has the plants
to process them into heroin.</i>

407
00:34:32,806 --> 00:34:36,207
<i>Now, he needs cash and he needs
protection from the police...</i>

408
00:34:36,310 --> 00:34:38,411
<i>for which he gives
a piece of the action.</i>

409
00:34:38,412 --> 00:34:40,413
<i>I couldn't find out how much.</i>

410
00:34:40,414 --> 00:34:43,212
<i>The Tattaglia family
is behind him here in New York.</i>

411
00:34:43,317 --> 00:34:45,485
<i>Now, they have to be
in it for something.</i>

412
00:34:45,486 --> 00:34:46,619
Santino Corleone.

413
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:48,488
What about his prison record?

414
00:34:48,489 --> 00:34:50,989
Two terms,
one in Italy, one here.

415
00:34:51,559 --> 00:34:54,059
He's known as
a top narcotics man.

416
00:34:54,061 --> 00:34:56,561
Santino, what do you think?

417
00:34:57,665 --> 00:35:00,165
There's a lot of money
in that white powder.

418
00:35:01,502 --> 00:35:02,802
Tom?

419
00:35:02,803 --> 00:35:05,303
<i>Well, I say, yes, there's more
money potential in narcotics...</i>

420
00:35:05,372 --> 00:35:07,373
<i>than anything else
we're looking at.</i>

421
00:35:07,374 --> 00:35:09,809
<i>Now, if we don't get into it,
somebody else will.</i>

422
00:35:09,810 --> 00:35:11,945
<i>Maybe one of the five families,
maybe all of them.</i>

423
00:35:11,946 --> 00:35:13,146
<i>Now, with the money they earn...</i>

424
00:35:13,147 --> 00:35:16,480
they can buy more police
and political power.

425
00:35:16,584 --> 00:35:18,785
Then they come after us.

426
00:35:18,786 --> 00:35:21,550
Now we have the unions,
we have the gambling...

427
00:35:21,655 --> 00:35:23,957
and they're the best things
to have, but narcotics...

428
00:35:23,958 --> 00:35:25,458
is a thing of the future.

429
00:35:25,459 --> 00:35:27,293
Now, if we don't get
a piece of that action...

430
00:35:27,294 --> 00:35:28,795
we risk everything we have.

431
00:35:28,796 --> 00:35:31,296
I mean, not now,
but ten years from now.

432
00:35:34,835 --> 00:35:37,929
So? What's your answer
gonna be, Pop?

433
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:49,180
I need a man
who has powerful friends.

434
00:35:50,084 --> 00:35:52,780
I need a million dollars in cash.

435
00:35:52,886 --> 00:35:54,988
I need, Don Corleone,
those politicians...

436
00:35:54,989 --> 00:35:58,652
that you carry in your pocket
like so many nickels and dimes.

437
00:36:00,227 --> 00:36:02,362
What is the interest
for my family?

438
00:36:02,363 --> 00:36:04,297
Thirty percent.

439
00:36:04,298 --> 00:36:07,096
In the first year, your end
should be three, four million dollars.

440
00:36:08,402 --> 00:36:10,902
And then it would go up.

441
00:36:11,505 --> 00:36:14,005
And what is the interest
for the Tattaglia family?

442
00:36:17,011 --> 00:36:19,511
My compliments.

443
00:36:22,316 --> 00:36:24,944
I'll take care of the Tattaglias.
Outta my share.

444
00:36:25,953 --> 00:36:28,649
So, I receive 30%
for finance...

445
00:36:30,190 --> 00:36:32,258
political influence
and legal protection.

446
00:36:32,259 --> 00:36:34,759
- That's what you're telling me.
- That's right.

447
00:36:36,664 --> 00:36:40,566
Why do you come to me?
Why do I deserve this generosity?

448
00:36:40,668 --> 00:36:43,603
If you consider
a million dollars in cash...

449
00:36:43,704 --> 00:36:45,904
just "finance"...

450
00:36:45,905 --> 00:36:47,905
<i>I salute you, Don Corleone.</i>

451
00:36:58,752 --> 00:37:01,687
I said that I would see you because...

452
00:37:01,789 --> 00:37:03,990
I heard that you were
a serious man...

453
00:37:03,991 --> 00:37:06,491
to be treated with respect.

454
00:37:11,131 --> 00:37:14,328
But I must say no to you.

455
00:37:15,502 --> 00:37:17,970
And I'll give you my reason.

456
00:37:17,971 --> 00:37:20,769
It's true, I have
a lot of friends in politics.

457
00:37:22,443 --> 00:37:24,444
But they wouldn't be friendly
very long...

458
00:37:24,445 --> 00:37:26,813
if they knew my business was drugs
instead of gambling...

459
00:37:26,814 --> 00:37:30,011
which they regard
as a harmless vice.

460
00:37:30,117 --> 00:37:32,745
- But drugs is a dirty business.
- No, Don Corleone...

461
00:37:32,853 --> 00:37:34,854
It doesn't make
any difference to me...

462
00:37:34,855 --> 00:37:37,619
what a man does for a living,
you understand...

463
00:37:37,725 --> 00:37:40,225
but your business is...

464
00:37:41,295 --> 00:37:43,029
a little dangerous.

465
00:37:43,030 --> 00:37:45,530
If you're worried about security
for your million...

466
00:37:45,532 --> 00:37:47,233
the Tattaglias will guarantee it.

467
00:37:47,234 --> 00:37:49,964
You're tellin' me the Tattaglias
guarantee our investment...

468
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:52,570
Wait a minute.

469
00:37:58,512 --> 00:38:00,646
I have a sentimental weakness
for my children...

470
00:38:00,647 --> 00:38:02,982
and I spoil them,
as you can see.

471
00:38:02,983 --> 00:38:04,684
They talk when they should listen.

472
00:38:04,685 --> 00:38:06,819
But anyway...

473
00:38:06,820 --> 00:38:09,320
Signor Sollozzo,
my no is final...

474
00:38:09,389 --> 00:38:12,187
and I wish to congratulate you
on your new business.

475
00:38:12,292 --> 00:38:15,557
I know you'll do very well,
and good luck to you...

476
00:38:15,662 --> 00:38:18,631
especially since your interests
don't conflict with mine.

477
00:38:20,067 --> 00:38:22,567
Thank you.

478
00:38:43,023 --> 00:38:45,523
Come here.

479
00:38:47,294 --> 00:38:49,128
What's the matter with you?

480
00:38:49,129 --> 00:38:50,930
I think your brain
is going soft...

481
00:38:50,931 --> 00:38:53,798
from all that comedy you're
playing with that young girl.

482
00:38:53,901 --> 00:38:57,302
Never tell anybody outside the
family what you're thinking again.

483
00:38:59,473 --> 00:39:01,973
Go on.

484
00:39:04,711 --> 00:39:07,441
Tom, what?
What is this nonsense?

485
00:39:07,548 --> 00:39:10,048
It's from Johnny.
He's starring in that new film.

486
00:39:12,719 --> 00:39:14,587
Well, take it away.

487
00:39:14,588 --> 00:39:17,088
Take it over there.

488
00:39:17,357 --> 00:39:19,826
And...

489
00:39:19,827 --> 00:39:22,327
tell Luca Brasi to come in.

490
00:39:28,168 --> 00:39:31,331
I'm a little worried
about this Sollozzo fellow.

491
00:39:31,438 --> 00:39:34,805
I want you to find out what he's got
under his fingernails, you know?

492
00:39:35,642 --> 00:39:37,710
Go to the Tattaglias...

493
00:39:37,711 --> 00:39:40,046
and make them think...

494
00:39:40,047 --> 00:39:43,744
that you're not too happy
with our family...

495
00:39:44,852 --> 00:39:47,352
and find out what you can.

496
00:40:04,171 --> 00:40:08,130
And I got something
for your mother and for Sonny...

497
00:40:08,242 --> 00:40:10,309
and a tie for Freddy...

498
00:40:10,310 --> 00:40:13,006
and Tom Hagen
got the Reynolds pen.

499
00:40:13,113 --> 00:40:15,214
- What do you want for Christmas?
- Me?

500
00:40:15,215 --> 00:40:17,715
Oh, just you.

501
00:40:50,050 --> 00:40:52,051
Tell Paulie to get the car.
We're going.

502
00:40:52,052 --> 00:40:53,486
Okay, Pa.

503
00:40:53,487 --> 00:40:56,388
I'll have to get it myself, Pa.
Paulie called in sick this morning.

504
00:40:59,393 --> 00:41:01,893
Paulie's a good kid.
I don't mind gettin' the car.

505
00:41:50,944 --> 00:41:54,402
Luca, I'm Bruno Tattaglia.

506
00:41:54,514 --> 00:41:55,982
I know.

507
00:41:55,983 --> 00:41:58,483
Scotch? Prewar.

508
00:42:04,658 --> 00:42:06,158
You know who I am?

509
00:43:45,293 --> 00:43:47,293
Oh. Tom Hagen.

510
00:43:47,294 --> 00:43:49,095
- Merry Christmas.
- Yeah.

511
00:43:49,096 --> 00:43:52,031
I'm glad I run into you.
I wanna talk to you.

512
00:43:52,132 --> 00:43:54,033
I haven't got time.

513
00:43:54,034 --> 00:43:56,798
Oh, make time, consigliere.
Get in the car.

514
00:43:58,905 --> 00:44:00,506
What are you worried about?

515
00:44:00,507 --> 00:44:03,007
If I wanted to kill you,
you'd be dead already.

516
00:44:03,810 --> 00:44:06,310
Get in.

517
00:44:16,491 --> 00:44:18,291
<i>Wait a moment, Fredo.</i>

518
00:44:18,492 --> 00:44:20,992
- I'm gonna buy some fruit.
- Okay, Pa.

519
00:44:26,133 --> 00:44:28,033
Hi. Merry Christmas.

520
00:44:28,034 --> 00:44:30,534
I want some fruit over there.

521
00:44:33,273 --> 00:44:35,773
Gimme three of them.

522
00:44:36,877 --> 00:44:39,377
No, that one.

523
00:44:57,497 --> 00:44:59,997
Fredo!

524
00:45:46,646 --> 00:45:49,146
Papa.

525
00:45:49,182 --> 00:45:51,682
Papa!

526
00:45:56,523 --> 00:45:59,287
Mike, would you like me better
if I were a nun...

527
00:45:59,392 --> 00:46:01,892
like in the story, you know?

528
00:46:04,131 --> 00:46:05,131
No.

529
00:46:05,232 --> 00:46:08,133
Well, then would you like me better
if I were Ingrid Bergman?

530
00:46:08,235 --> 00:46:10,735
Now that's a thought.

531
00:46:12,106 --> 00:46:13,106
Michael.

532
00:46:13,807 --> 00:46:17,038
No, I would not like you better
if you were Ingrid Bergman.

533
00:46:17,143 --> 00:46:19,643
- Michael.
- What's the matter?

534
00:46:35,428 --> 00:46:37,928
They don't say
if he's dead or alive.

535
00:47:00,120 --> 00:47:02,048
Sonny, Michael.

536
00:47:02,049 --> 00:47:03,449
<i>Michael, where you been?</i>

537
00:47:03,556 --> 00:47:05,224
Is he all right?

538
00:47:05,225 --> 00:47:07,955
<i>We don't know yet.
There's all kinds of stories.</i>

539
00:47:09,496 --> 00:47:11,996
<i>He was hit bad, Mikey.</i>

540
00:47:12,432 --> 00:47:15,560
<i>- Are you there?
- Yeah, I'm here.</i>

541
00:47:15,669 --> 00:47:18,103
<i>Where you been? I was worried.</i>

542
00:47:18,104 --> 00:47:20,272
Didn't Tom tell you?
I called.

543
00:47:20,273 --> 00:47:24,004
<i>No. Look, come home, kid.
You should be with Mama, you hear?</i>

544
00:47:24,110 --> 00:47:26,610
All right.

545
00:47:32,319 --> 00:47:34,819
Oh, my God.

546
00:47:48,802 --> 00:47:51,302
Who is it?

547
00:47:51,404 --> 00:47:53,904
Open up. It's Clemenza.

548
00:47:54,908 --> 00:47:55,974
What?

549
00:47:55,975 --> 00:47:58,475
There's more news about your old man.

550
00:47:58,945 --> 00:48:01,013
The word is out on the street
he's already dead.

551
00:48:01,014 --> 00:48:03,015
Shut your mouth.
What's the matter with you?

552
00:48:03,016 --> 00:48:05,516
Jesus Christ!
Take it easy. Take it easy.

553
00:48:05,552 --> 00:48:07,753
- Where was Paulie?
- Paulie was out sick.

554
00:48:07,754 --> 00:48:10,274
- He's been home sick all winter.
- How many times he been sick?

555
00:48:10,323 --> 00:48:11,890
Only maybe three, four times.

556
00:48:11,891 --> 00:48:13,959
I mean, I asked Freddy if he wants
a different bodyguard.

557
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,694
- He said no.
- Pick him up right now.

558
00:48:15,695 --> 00:48:17,529
I don't care how sick he is.

559
00:48:17,530 --> 00:48:20,192
If he's breathin', I want you to bring him to
my father's house now. You understand? Now

560
00:48:20,300 --> 00:48:23,098
- You want me to send people here?
- No, just you and him. Go ahead.

561
00:48:23,203 --> 00:48:25,703
All right.

562
00:48:32,712 --> 00:48:35,913
I'm havin' a couple of our people come
over to the house. A couple of our people.

563
00:48:39,519 --> 00:48:41,787
<i>- Hello?
- Santino Corleone?</i>

564
00:48:41,788 --> 00:48:44,288
<i>- Yeah.
- We have Tom Hagen.</i>

565
00:48:44,958 --> 00:48:48,394
<i>In about three hours, he'll be
released with our proposition.</i>

566
00:48:48,495 --> 00:48:51,862
<i>Listen to everything he has
to say before you do anything.</i>

567
00:48:51,965 --> 00:48:53,599
<i>What's done is done.</i>

568
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:56,569
<i>And don't lose that famous temper
of yours, huh, Sonny?</i>

569
00:48:56,669 --> 00:48:59,169
No, I'll wait.

570
00:49:12,685 --> 00:49:15,185
Your boss is dead.

571
00:49:17,524 --> 00:49:19,992
I know you're not in the muscle
end of the family, Tom...

572
00:49:19,993 --> 00:49:22,493
so I don't want you to be scared.

573
00:49:23,062 --> 00:49:25,587
I want you
to help the Corleones...

574
00:49:25,698 --> 00:49:28,198
and I want you to help me.

575
00:49:30,770 --> 00:49:32,604
Yeah. We got him outside his office...

576
00:49:32,605 --> 00:49:35,105
just about an hour after we picked you up.

577
00:49:36,943 --> 00:49:39,443
Drink it.

578
00:49:42,582 --> 00:49:46,018
So now it's up to you to make
the peace between me and Sonny.

579
00:49:50,557 --> 00:49:53,057
Sonny was hot
for my deal, wasn't he?

580
00:49:54,461 --> 00:49:56,961
And you knew it was
the right thing to do.

581
00:49:58,798 --> 00:50:01,298
Sonny will come after you
with everything he's got.

582
00:50:02,068 --> 00:50:04,568
That'll be his first reaction, sure.

583
00:50:05,338 --> 00:50:07,739
That's why you gotta
talk some sense into him.

584
00:50:07,740 --> 00:50:10,971
The Tattaglia family is behind me
with all their people.

585
00:50:11,945 --> 00:50:14,112
The other New York families
will go along with anything...

586
00:50:14,113 --> 00:50:16,613
that will prevent a full-scale war.

587
00:50:17,183 --> 00:50:19,551
Let's face it, Tom,
in all due respect...

588
00:50:19,552 --> 00:50:22,112
the Don, rest in peace, was slippin'.

589
00:50:25,024 --> 00:50:27,524
Ten years ago,
could I have gotten to him?

590
00:50:31,998 --> 00:50:33,565
Well, now he's dead.

591
00:50:33,566 --> 00:50:36,066
He's dead, Tom,
and nothing can bring him back.

592
00:50:37,704 --> 00:50:39,838
So you gotta talk to Sonny.

593
00:50:39,839 --> 00:50:41,773
You gotta talk
to the caporegimes...

594
00:50:41,774 --> 00:50:44,274
that Tessio, and that fat Clemenza.

595
00:50:48,681 --> 00:50:51,181
It's good business, Tom.

596
00:50:52,118 --> 00:50:54,419
I'll try.

597
00:50:54,420 --> 00:50:57,082
But even Sonny won't be able
to call off Luca Brasi.

598
00:51:00,093 --> 00:51:02,593
Yeah. Well...

599
00:51:03,396 --> 00:51:05,896
Let me worry about Luca.

600
00:51:11,304 --> 00:51:13,205
You just talk to Sonny.

601
00:51:13,206 --> 00:51:15,706
And the other two kids.

602
00:51:18,945 --> 00:51:20,445
I'll do my best.

603
00:51:20,446 --> 00:51:22,946
Good.

604
00:51:23,750 --> 00:51:26,250
Now, you can go.

605
00:51:33,126 --> 00:51:36,459
I don't like violence, Tom.
I'm a businessman.

606
00:51:37,997 --> 00:51:40,497
Blood is a big expense.

607
00:52:01,588 --> 00:52:03,488
He's still alive.

608
00:52:03,489 --> 00:52:05,989
They hit him with five shots,
and he's still alive!

609
00:52:07,493 --> 00:52:09,494
Well, that's bad luck for me...

610
00:52:09,495 --> 00:52:11,995
and bad luck for you
if you don't make that deal.

611
00:52:56,976 --> 00:52:59,044
Your mother's over
in the hospital with your father.

612
00:52:59,045 --> 00:53:01,545
Looks like he's gonna
pull through, thank God.

613
00:53:03,616 --> 00:53:05,884
- That's a lot of bad blood.
- What do you think?

614
00:53:05,885 --> 00:53:08,752
It's too far.
I think it's too personal.

615
00:53:08,855 --> 00:53:11,517
- The Don will consider this over.
- You gonna kill all those guys?

616
00:53:11,624 --> 00:53:14,124
- Hey, stay out of it, Mickey, do me a favor.
- Sollozzo's the key.

617
00:53:14,127 --> 00:53:16,428
You get rid of him,
everything falls into line.

618
00:53:16,429 --> 00:53:19,023
What about Luca? Sollozzo
didn't seem worried about Luca.

619
00:53:20,733 --> 00:53:24,499
I don't know. If Luca sold out,
we're in a lot of trouble.

620
00:53:24,604 --> 00:53:26,672
Has anyone been able
to get in touch with Luca?

621
00:53:26,673 --> 00:53:28,774
We've been tryin' all night.
He might be shacked up.

622
00:53:28,775 --> 00:53:29,841
Hey, Mick, try him again.

623
00:53:29,842 --> 00:53:31,510
Luca never sleeps over
with a broad.

624
00:53:31,511 --> 00:53:34,011
He always goes home
when he's through.

625
00:53:34,547 --> 00:53:37,516
Well, Tom, you're consigliere.

626
00:53:37,617 --> 00:53:40,745
What do we do
if the old man dies, God forbid?

627
00:53:40,853 --> 00:53:43,353
If we lose the old man...

628
00:53:44,123 --> 00:53:47,058
we lose our political contacts
and half our strength.

629
00:53:47,160 --> 00:53:50,061
The other New York families might
wind up supporting Sollozzo...

630
00:53:50,163 --> 00:53:52,531
just to avoid a long destructive war.

631
00:53:52,532 --> 00:53:56,263
This is almost 1946.
Nobody wants bloodshed anymore.

632
00:53:57,503 --> 00:54:00,003
If your father dies...

633
00:54:01,340 --> 00:54:03,108
you'll make the deal, Sonny.

634
00:54:03,109 --> 00:54:05,669
You know, that's easy for you to say,
Tom. He's not your father.

635
00:54:05,778 --> 00:54:08,278
I was as much a son to him
as you or Mike.

636
00:54:12,719 --> 00:54:15,219
What is it?

637
00:54:15,221 --> 00:54:17,689
Hey, Paulie, I thought
I told you to stay put.

638
00:54:17,690 --> 00:54:20,318
Well, the guy at the gates,
they say they got a package.

639
00:54:20,426 --> 00:54:22,926
Yeah?
Tessio, go see what it is.

640
00:54:26,299 --> 00:54:28,300
- You want me to hang around?
- Yeah, hang around.

641
00:54:28,301 --> 00:54:29,801
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

642
00:54:29,802 --> 00:54:32,498
Yeah? There's some food
in the icebox. You hungry or anything?

643
00:54:32,605 --> 00:54:34,673
- No, it's all right. Thanks.
- How 'bout a drink? How 'bout a little brandy?

644
00:54:34,674 --> 00:54:36,441
- That's good to sweat it out.
- All right, sure.

645
00:54:36,442 --> 00:54:38,942
- Go ahead.
- That might be a good idea.

646
00:54:40,646 --> 00:54:43,146
I want you to take care
of that son of a bitch right away.

647
00:54:43,182 --> 00:54:45,707
Paulie sold out the old man, that strutz.

648
00:54:45,818 --> 00:54:48,912
I don't wanna see him again. Make that
first thing on your list, understand?

649
00:54:49,021 --> 00:54:50,355
Understood.

650
00:54:50,356 --> 00:54:52,691
Hey, Mickey, tomorrow.
You get a couple of guys.

651
00:54:52,692 --> 00:54:54,893
You go over to Luca's apartment. Hang
around. Wait for him to show up.

652
00:54:54,894 --> 00:54:58,955
Maybe we shouldn't get Mike
mixed up in this too directly.

653
00:54:59,065 --> 00:55:01,333
Yeah.

654
00:55:01,334 --> 00:55:04,861
Listen, hang around the house
on the phone. It'll be a big help.

655
00:55:05,972 --> 00:55:08,472
Try Luca again. Go ahead.

656
00:55:16,816 --> 00:55:19,649
- What the hell is this?
- It's a Sicilian message.

657
00:55:19,752 --> 00:55:22,252
It means Luca Brasi sleeps with the fishes.

658
00:55:36,035 --> 00:55:38,535
- I'm goin' now.
- What time you gonna be home tonight?

659
00:55:38,571 --> 00:55:41,071
I don't know. Probably late.

660
00:55:42,341 --> 00:55:45,868
- Don't forget the cannoli.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

661
00:55:48,581 --> 00:55:52,381
Rocco, sit on the other side.
You block the rearview mirror.

662
00:55:54,554 --> 00:55:56,121
That Sonny's runnin' wild.

663
00:55:56,122 --> 00:55:58,190
He's thinkin' of goin'
to the mattresses already.

664
00:55:58,191 --> 00:56:00,751
We gotta find a spot
over on the West Side.

665
00:56:00,860 --> 00:56:03,954
We'll try 309 West 43rd Street.

666
00:56:04,063 --> 00:56:06,431
You know any good spots
on the West Side?

667
00:56:06,432 --> 00:56:08,932
- Yeah, I'll think about it.
- Well, think about it while you're drivin'.

668
00:56:08,968 --> 00:56:11,303
I wanna hit New York sometime this month.

669
00:56:11,304 --> 00:56:13,804
And watch out for the kids
when you're backin' out.

670
00:56:24,183 --> 00:56:26,618
Hey, Paulie, I want you to go
down 39th Street. Colosanto's.

671
00:56:26,619 --> 00:56:29,679
You pick up 18 mattresses for the guys
to sleep, will you? Bring me the bill.

672
00:56:29,789 --> 00:56:32,690
- Yeah, all right.
- Make sure they're clean because...

673
00:56:32,792 --> 00:56:35,989
Those guys are gonna be stuck up
in there for a long time, you know?

674
00:56:36,095 --> 00:56:38,296
They're clean. They told me
they exterminate them.

675
00:56:38,297 --> 00:56:40,398
"Exterminate"?
That's a bad word to use.

676
00:56:40,399 --> 00:56:43,368
Exterminate. Get this guy.
See how we don't exterminate you.

677
00:56:43,469 --> 00:56:45,969
<i>- Youse funny, or what?
- Hey, Paulie. Did you fart?</i>

678
00:56:47,173 --> 00:56:49,673
- Yeah, Rocco, what'd you do?
- No, me. Nothin'. It wasn't me.

679
00:56:49,742 --> 00:56:51,810
- It's gotta be him.
- Hey, pull over, will you.

680
00:56:51,811 --> 00:56:54,311
I gotta take a leak.

681
00:57:35,521 --> 00:57:37,322
Leave the gun.

682
00:57:37,323 --> 00:57:39,823
Take the cannoli.

683
00:57:56,612 --> 00:57:58,112
<i>Hey, Mike?</i>

684
00:57:58,613 --> 00:58:00,113
<i>Hey, Mikey?</i>

685
00:58:01,614 --> 00:58:02,614
Yeah?

686
00:58:02,714 --> 00:58:04,114
<i>You're wanted on the telephone.</i>

687
00:58:09,822 --> 00:58:12,322
- Who is it?
- It's some girl.

688
00:58:16,395 --> 00:58:17,595
Hello, Kay?

689
00:58:17,596 --> 00:58:18,964
<i>How's your father?</i>

690
00:58:18,965 --> 00:58:20,765
He's good.
He's gonna make it.

691
00:58:20,766 --> 00:58:23,266
<i>I love you.</i>

692
00:58:23,267 --> 00:58:24,267
Huh?

693
00:58:24,570 --> 00:58:26,570
<i>I love you!</i>

694
00:58:26,806 --> 00:58:28,307
<i>Michael?</i>

695
00:58:28,708 --> 00:58:29,708
Yeah, I know.

696
00:58:29,709 --> 00:58:31,509
<i>Tell me you love me.</i>

697
00:58:31,510 --> 00:58:33,210
Yeah, I can't talk.

698
00:58:33,211 --> 00:58:35,011
<i>Can't you say it?</i>

699
00:58:35,815 --> 00:58:38,315
Yeah, I'll see you tonight.

700
00:58:38,517 --> 00:58:41,509
Hey, Mikey. Why don't you tell
that nice girl you love her?

701
00:58:41,620 --> 00:58:43,688
I love you
with all o' my heart!

702
00:58:43,689 --> 00:58:46,214
If I don't see you again a-soon,
I'm-a gonna die!

703
00:58:47,460 --> 00:58:49,461
Come over here, kid.
Learn somethin'.

704
00:58:49,462 --> 00:58:51,962
You never know. You might have to cook
for 20 guys someday.

705
00:58:52,465 --> 00:58:54,799
You see? You start out
with a little bit of oil.

706
00:58:54,800 --> 00:58:56,368
Then you fry some garlic.

707
00:58:56,369 --> 00:58:58,997
Then you throw in some tomatoes,
some tomato paste.

708
00:58:59,105 --> 00:59:01,767
You fry it.
You make sure it doesn't stick.

709
00:59:01,874 --> 00:59:05,037
When you got it to a boil, you shove in
all your sausage and your meatballs.

710
00:59:07,913 --> 00:59:10,413
Add a little bit of wine.

711
00:59:13,252 --> 00:59:16,153
And a little bit of sugar.

712
00:59:16,922 --> 00:59:18,923
- And that's my trick.
- Why don't you cut the crap?

713
00:59:18,924 --> 00:59:21,092
I got more important things
for you to do.

714
00:59:21,093 --> 00:59:23,687
- How's Paulie?
- Oh, Paulie. Won't see him no more.

715
00:59:25,765 --> 00:59:28,265
- Where you going?
- To the city.

716
00:59:28,267 --> 00:59:29,934
Send some bodyguards with him.

717
00:59:29,935 --> 00:59:31,936
- No. I'm just going to the hospital to see Pop.
- Nevermind. Send somebody with him.

718
00:59:31,937 --> 00:59:34,838
Oh, he'll be all right.
Sollozzo knows he's a civilian.

719
00:59:34,940 --> 00:59:37,440
- All right. Be careful, huh?
- Yes, sir.

720
00:59:40,446 --> 00:59:42,946
Send somebody with him anyway.

721
01:00:11,143 --> 01:00:12,977
I have to go.

722
01:00:12,978 --> 01:00:15,478
Can I go with you?

723
01:00:15,815 --> 01:00:18,375
No, Kay. There's gonna be
detectives there.

724
01:00:18,484 --> 01:00:20,485
People from the press.

725
01:00:20,486 --> 01:00:22,986
Well, I'll ride in a cab.

726
01:00:24,990 --> 01:00:27,490
I don't want you to get involved.

727
01:00:30,162 --> 01:00:32,662
When will I see you again?

728
01:00:38,838 --> 01:00:40,839
Go back to New Hampshire...

729
01:00:40,840 --> 01:00:43,340
and I'll call you
at your parents' house.

730
01:00:44,677 --> 01:00:47,177
When will I see you again,
Michael?

731
01:00:48,681 --> 01:00:51,181
I don't know.

732
01:03:01,213 --> 01:03:03,348
What are you doing here?

733
01:03:03,349 --> 01:03:05,450
You're not supposed
to be here now.

734
01:03:05,451 --> 01:03:09,012
I'm Michael Corleone.
This is my father.

735
01:03:09,121 --> 01:03:11,681
There's nobody here.
What happened to the guards?

736
01:03:11,790 --> 01:03:14,125
Your father just had
