straighten everything out.

974
01:21:34,492 --> 01:21:37,359
I mean, this is terrible. It's not the way
I wanted things to go at all.

975
01:21:37,462 --> 01:21:39,329
It should have never happened.

976
01:21:39,330 --> 01:21:41,498
I want to straighten
everything out tonight.

977
01:21:41,499 --> 01:21:43,999
I don't want my father
bothered anymore.

978
01:21:44,001 --> 01:21:48,062
He won't be, Mike.
I swear on my children he won't be.

979
01:21:48,172 --> 01:21:51,403
But you got to keep an open mind
when we talk.

980
01:21:51,509 --> 01:21:54,009
I mean, I hope you're not a hot-head
like your brother Sonny.

981
01:21:54,011 --> 01:21:56,511
You can't talk business
with him.

982
01:21:57,682 --> 01:22:00,182
He's a good kid.

983
01:22:03,521 --> 01:22:06,021
I'm sorry about
the other night, Mike.

984
01:22:07,125 --> 01:22:09,625
I gotta frisk you,
so turn around, huh?

985
01:22:09,627 --> 01:22:12,127
On your knees, facing me.

986
01:22:15,967 --> 01:22:18,868
I guess I'm getting
too old for my job.

987
01:22:19,971 --> 01:22:22,038
Too grouchy.

988
01:22:22,039 --> 01:22:24,701
Can't stand the aggravation.

989
01:22:24,809 --> 01:22:27,309
You know how it is.

990
01:22:28,146 --> 01:22:30,646
He's clean.

991
01:22:56,507 --> 01:22:59,007
We're going to Jersey?

992
01:23:00,678 --> 01:23:03,178
Maybe.

993
01:23:27,805 --> 01:23:30,305
Nice work, Lou.

994
01:24:06,978 --> 01:24:09,045
How's the Italian food
in this restaurant?

995
01:24:09,046 --> 01:24:11,481
Good.
Try the veal.

996
01:24:11,482 --> 01:24:13,982
- It's the best in the city.
- I'll have it.

997
01:24:15,483 --> 01:24:17,483
<i>Understand?</i>

998
01:24:49,987 --> 01:24:51,855
I'm gonna speak Italian to Mike.

999
01:24:51,856 --> 01:24:54,356
Go ahead.

1000
01:24:59,256 --> 01:25:01,756
- I'm sorry.
- Forget about it.

1001
01:25:04,757 --> 01:25:10,757
What happened to
your father was business.

1002
01:25:12,758 --> 01:25:15,758
I have much respect for your father...

1003
01:25:15,759 --> 01:25:19,759
but your father's thinking
is old fashioned.

1004
01:25:20,760 --> 01:25:24,760
You must understand why
I did what I did.

1005
01:25:25,761 --> 01:25:28,761
I understand these things.

1006
01:25:29,262 --> 01:25:30,962
I do.

1007
01:25:30,963 --> 01:25:33,463
You do.

1008
01:25:43,964 --> 01:25:47,964
Now we have to think about what happens

1009
01:25:48,265 --> 01:25:52,165
between you and the Tattaglias.

1010
01:25:52,965 --> 01:25:56,965
We have to work through

1011
01:25:56,966 --> 01:26:00,966
where we go from here.

1012
01:26:08,466 --> 01:26:10,966
How do I say...?

1013
01:26:12,770 --> 01:26:15,270
What I want...

1014
01:26:15,439 --> 01:26:17,939
what's most important to me...

1015
01:26:20,277 --> 01:26:22,445
is that I have a guarantee:

1016
01:26:22,446 --> 01:26:24,614
no more attempts
on my father's life.

1017
01:26:24,615 --> 01:26:28,847
What guarantees could I give you, Mike?
I am the hunted one.

1018
01:26:29,453 --> 01:26:32,513
I missed my chance.
You think too much of me, kid.

1019
01:26:32,623 --> 01:26:35,123
I'm not that clever.

1020
01:26:36,293 --> 01:26:38,793
All I want is a truce.

1021
01:26:45,302 --> 01:26:48,999
I have to go to the bathroom.
Is that all right?

1022
01:26:50,307 --> 01:26:52,807
You gotta go, you gotta go.

1023
01:26:58,449 --> 01:27:00,083
I frisked him.
He's clean.

1024
01:27:00,084 --> 01:27:02,584
Don't take too long.

1025
01:27:05,756 --> 01:27:08,256
I've frisked a thousand young punks.

1026
01:28:23,554 --> 01:28:26,054
Everything all right?

1027
01:28:27,055 --> 01:28:29,555
I respect myself...  understand?

1028
01:28:29,556 --> 01:28:32,556
And so I cannot allow your
father to hold me back.

1029
01:28:33,357 --> 01:28:36,357
What happened was unavoidable.

1030
01:28:37,358 --> 01:28:39,858
I had the unspoken support of
the other Dons.

1031
01:28:39,859 --> 01:28:42,359
If your father were in better health...

1032
01:28:42,360 --> 01:28:44,860
without his eldest son running things...

1033
01:30:58,689 --> 01:31:00,189
Hey, come on.

1034
01:31:00,190 --> 01:31:02,690
Come on. Let's go.

1035
01:31:58,349 --> 01:32:00,849
Joe, you take over.

1036
01:32:03,687 --> 01:32:06,187
Hi, Grandpa.

1037
01:32:17,634 --> 01:32:20,134
I love you, Grandpa.

1038
01:32:22,139 --> 01:32:24,869
I'm sorry, Pa.
He doesn't know you yet.

1039
01:32:26,610 --> 01:32:29,474
- Here you are, big guy. Give it to Grandpa.
- Okay.

1040
01:32:29,480 --> 01:32:31,647
"I hope you get red, Grandpa...

1041
01:32:31,648 --> 01:32:33,649
and I wish
I would see you soon.

1042
01:32:33,650 --> 01:32:36,150
Love, your grandson, Frank."

1043
01:32:38,655 --> 01:32:40,990
Go with your mother.

1044
01:32:40,991 --> 01:32:43,491
Go ahead.
Take 'em downstairs.

1045
01:32:49,166 --> 01:32:51,666
Go on, Carlo. You too.

1046
01:32:53,003 --> 01:32:55,503
Go on.

1047
01:32:58,008 --> 01:33:01,239
I got chicken cacciatore
for you, sweetheart.

1048
01:33:01,345 --> 01:33:03,246
- That's enough bread.
- I like bread.

1049
01:33:03,247 --> 01:33:05,747
I know, but how much can you eat?

1050
01:33:15,292 --> 01:33:17,293
What's the matter with you, Carlo?

1051
01:33:17,294 --> 01:33:19,794
Shut up and set the table.

1052
01:33:34,978 --> 01:33:37,538
Since McCluskey's killing...

1053
01:33:37,648 --> 01:33:41,049
the police have been cracking down
most of our operations.

1054
01:33:42,820 --> 01:33:45,320
And also the other families'.

1055
01:33:45,823 --> 01:33:47,623
Been a lot of bad blood.

1056
01:33:47,624 --> 01:33:51,116
They hit us, so we hit them back.

1057
01:33:51,995 --> 01:33:54,163
Through our contacts
in the newspapers...

1058
01:33:54,164 --> 01:33:56,499
we've been able to put out
a lot of material...

1059
01:33:56,500 --> 01:33:59,901
about McCluskey being linked
with Sollozzo in the drug rackets.

1060
01:34:01,171 --> 01:34:03,671
See, things are
starting to loosen up.

1061
01:34:04,274 --> 01:34:09,007
Dad, I'm sending Fredo
to Las Vegas...

1062
01:34:09,113 --> 01:34:11,707
under the protection
of Don Francesco of L.A.

1063
01:34:11,815 --> 01:34:13,783
I want him to rest.

1064
01:34:13,784 --> 01:34:16,284
I'm going to learn
the casino business.

1065
01:34:16,286 --> 01:34:18,786
Yeah.

1066
01:34:24,461 --> 01:34:26,961
Where is Michael?

1067
01:34:38,809 --> 01:34:41,403
It was Michael who killed Sollozzo.

1068
01:34:43,814 --> 01:34:47,545
But he's safe. We're starting
to work to bring him back now.

1069
01:35:09,273 --> 01:35:11,440
I want you to find out where that
little pimp Tattaglia is hiding.

1070
01:35:11,441 --> 01:35:13,442
I want his ass now...
right now.

1071
01:35:13,443 --> 01:35:15,278
- Hey, Sonny.
- What?

1072
01:35:15,279 --> 01:35:17,113
Things are starting to loosen up
a little bit.

1073
01:35:17,114 --> 01:35:19,844
If you go after Tattaglia,
all hell's going to break loose.

1074
01:35:19,950 --> 01:35:21,951
Let the smoke clear.
Pop can negotiate.

1075
01:35:21,952 --> 01:35:24,452
No, Pop can't do nothing till
he's better. I'm gonna decide what...

1076
01:35:24,454 --> 01:35:26,455
All right, but your war's
costing us a lot of money.

1077
01:35:26,456 --> 01:35:28,291
Nothing's coming in.
We can't do business.

1078
01:35:28,292 --> 01:35:31,022
Well neither can they.
Don't worry about it.

1079
01:35:31,128 --> 01:35:33,129
- We can't afford a stalemate.
- Well, then there ain't no more stalemate.

1080
01:35:33,130 --> 01:35:35,131
I'm gonna end it
by killing that old bastard.

1081
01:35:35,132 --> 01:35:37,300
You're getting a great reputation.
I hope you're enjoying it.

1082
01:35:37,301 --> 01:35:38,968
Well you just do what I tell you to do!

1083
01:35:38,969 --> 01:35:41,137
Goddamn it, if I had a wartime
consigliere, a Sicilian,

1084
01:35:41,138 --> 01:35:43,139
I wouldn't be in this shape!

1085
01:35:43,140 --> 01:35:45,640
Pop had Genco. Look what I got.

1086
01:35:48,979 --> 01:35:51,479
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean that.

1087
01:35:52,482 --> 01:35:55,508
Mom made a little dinner.
It's Sunday.

1088
01:35:56,486 --> 01:35:59,216
Them niggers are having
a good time...

1089
01:35:59,323 --> 01:36:00,990
with our policy banks
up there in Harlem.

1090
01:36:00,991 --> 01:36:04,825
Driving them new Cadillacs,
paying 50% on a bet.

1091
01:36:04,928 --> 01:36:08,329
I knew that was gonna happen as soon
as they started making big money.

1092
01:36:08,432 --> 01:36:11,993
Look, Papa never talked business
at the table in front of the kids.

1093
01:36:12,102 --> 01:36:14,832
- Hey, shut up, Connie.
- Don't you ever tell her to shut up.

1094
01:36:14,938 --> 01:36:17,998
- You got that?
- Santino, don't interfere.

1095
01:36:19,943 --> 01:36:22,543
You know, Sonny, Tom, I'd like to talk
to you, maybe after dinner.

1096
01:36:22,613 --> 01:36:24,614
I could be doing a lot more
for the family.

1097
01:36:24,615 --> 01:36:27,115
We don't discuss business
at the table.

1098
01:37:20,037 --> 01:37:21,537
Michael

1099
01:37:52,038 --> 01:37:54,538
Corleone.

1100
01:38:24,039 --> 01:38:26,039
Look there. Corleone.

1101
01:39:03,376 --> 01:39:06,709
Hey, American!
Take me to the America! G.I.!

1102
01:39:07,276 --> 01:39:08,276
Hey, hey, hey!

1103
01:39:08,315 --> 01:39:11,375
Take me to America, G.I.
Clark Gable.

1104
01:39:11,876 --> 01:39:13,376
America! America!

1105
01:39:13,377 --> 01:39:14,877
Take me to the America, G.I.

1106
01:39:14,878 --> 01:39:16,878
Clark Gable.
Rita Hayworth.

1107
01:40:10,196 --> 01:40:12,196
Hey, host.

1108
01:40:13,897 --> 01:40:15,897
A bottle of wine.

1109
01:42:11,197 --> 01:42:13,697
I apologize if I offended you.

1110
01:42:14,534 --> 01:42:17,034
I'm a stranger in this country...

1111
01:42:17,537 --> 01:42:20,438
and I meant no disrespect
to you or your daughter.

1112
01:42:26,212 --> 01:42:28,712
I'm an American hiding in Sicily.

1113
01:42:30,383 --> 01:42:32,883
My name is Michael Corleone.

1114
01:42:34,721 --> 01:42:37,362
There are people who would pay
a lot of money for that information.

1115
01:42:41,227 --> 01:42:43,727
But then your daughter
would lose a father...

1116
01:42:45,665 --> 01:42:48,165
instead of gaining a husband.

1117
01:42:55,909 --> 01:42:58,409
I want to meet your daughter...

1118
01:42:59,245 --> 01:43:01,079
with your permission...

1119
01:43:01,080 --> 01:43:03,580
and under the supervision
of your family...

1120
01:43:04,517 --> 01:43:07,017
with all respect.

1121
01:43:24,704 --> 01:43:27,204
Apollonia.

1122
01:44:21,705 --> 01:44:24,705
...this is my daughter, Apollonia...

1123
01:44:24,706 --> 01:44:27,706
and this is Michael Corleone.

1124
01:44:43,707 --> 01:44:45,707
Thank you.

1125
01:44:46,308 --> 01:44:48,308
Your welcome.

1126
01:44:58,309 --> 01:45:00,809
What's the problem with your eye.

1127
01:45:01,310 --> 01:45:03,810
No, no. It's nothing. It's fine.

1128
01:46:18,511 --> 01:46:21,011
Hey! I'm gonna knock you dizzy.

1129
01:46:26,519 --> 01:46:29,019
Save it for the library.

1130
01:46:32,158 --> 01:46:34,658
Come on. We gotta go
pick up my sister. Let's go.

1131
01:46:52,879 --> 01:46:55,379
What's the matter?

1132
01:46:57,180 --> 01:46:59,180
What's the matter?

1133
01:47:00,386 --> 01:47:02,554
- It was my fault!
- Where is he?

1134
01:47:02,555 --> 01:47:05,956
Sonny, please. It was my fault.
Sonny, it was my fault. I hit him.

1135
01:47:06,059 --> 01:47:07,993
I started a fight with him.
Please, Sonny.

1136
01:47:07,994 --> 01:47:10,494
I'm sorry.

1137
01:47:14,468 --> 01:47:17,798
Okay, I'm just... I'm just gonna get a
doctor to come and take a look at you.

1138
01:47:18,004 --> 01:47:20,734
Sonny, please don't do anything.
Please, don't do it.

1139
01:47:22,842 --> 01:47:25,010
What's the matter with you?
What am I gonna do?

1140
01:47:25,011 --> 01:47:27,809
Am I gonna make that baby an orphan
before he's born?

1141
01:47:30,683 --> 01:47:32,184
All right?

1142
01:47:32,185 --> 01:47:35,279
Still betting the Yankees
pretty heavy?

1143
01:47:35,388 --> 01:47:37,888
Tell him to stop
taking action, all right?

1144
01:47:39,058 --> 01:47:41,558
You lost enough money
last weekend to me.

1145
01:47:47,433 --> 01:47:49,933
Carlo, come here.

1146
01:48:47,026 --> 01:48:49,756
You touch my sister again,
I'll kill you.

1147
01:52:45,097 --> 01:52:47,827
Weren't expecting you, Kay.
You should call.

1148
01:52:47,933 --> 01:52:52,233
Yes, well, I have.
I mean I've tried writing and calling.

1149
01:52:52,338 --> 01:52:54,706
Now, I wanna reach Michael.

1150
01:52:54,707 --> 01:52:58,108
Nobody knows where he is. We know
that he's all right, but that's all.

1151
01:53:01,380 --> 01:53:03,381
- What was that?
- That's an accident.

1152
01:53:03,382 --> 01:53:06,078
But nobody was hurt.

1153
01:53:06,152 --> 01:53:07,152
Tom...

1154
01:53:07,653 --> 01:53:11,487
Would you give this letter
to Michael, please? Please?

1155
01:53:11,590 --> 01:53:13,925
Well, if I accepted that...

1156
01:53:13,926 --> 01:53:17,487
in a court of law they could prove that
I have knowledge of his whereabouts.

1157
01:53:17,596 --> 01:53:19,798
Now you just be patient, Kay.
He'll get in touch with you, all right?

1158
01:53:19,799 --> 01:53:23,701
I let my cab go, so can I come in
to call another one, please?

1159
01:53:23,803 --> 01:53:26,303
Come on. I'm sorry.
Come on.

1160
01:53:42,621 --> 01:53:45,121
Hello?

1161
01:53:46,692 --> 01:53:48,460
<i>Is Carlo there?</i>

1162
01:53:48,461 --> 01:53:50,929
<i>- Who's this?
- This is a friend of Carlo's.</i>

1163
01:53:50,930 --> 01:53:53,990
<i>Would you tell him that
I can't make it tonight until later?</i>

1164
01:54:00,206 --> 01:54:02,706
Bitch.

1165
01:54:03,476 --> 01:54:06,070
- Dinner's on the table.
- I'm not hungry yet.

1166
01:54:06,178 --> 01:54:08,179
Your food is on the table.
It's getting cold.

1167
01:54:08,180 --> 01:54:11,240
- I'll eat out later.
- You just told me to make you dinner.

1168
01:54:11,350 --> 01:54:13,351
Hey, fuck you, eh?

1169
01:54:13,352 --> 01:54:15,852
Go fuck yourself!

1170
01:54:20,559 --> 01:54:23,059
This little guinea brat.

1171
01:54:27,466 --> 01:54:30,060
That's it. Break it all,
you spoiled guinea brat.

1172
01:54:30,169 --> 01:54:32,669
Break it all!

1173
01:54:35,374 --> 01:54:37,874
That's it. Break it all.

1174
01:54:40,980 --> 01:54:45,178
Why don't you bring
your whore home for dinner?

1175
01:54:45,284 --> 01:54:47,784
Maybe I will.
Why not?

1176
01:54:53,459 --> 01:54:55,927
- Now clean it up!
- Like hell I will!

1177
01:54:55,928 --> 01:54:58,428
Clean it up,
you guinea spoiled brat!

1178
01:54:58,430 --> 01:55:00,930
Clean it up!
Clean it up!

1179
01:55:05,337 --> 01:55:07,837
You son of a bitch!

1180
01:55:16,515 --> 01:55:19,609
Come on, now! Kill me!
Be a murderer like your father!

1181
01:55:19,718 --> 01:55:22,053
- Come on! All you Corleones are murderers!
- I hate you!

1182
01:55:22,054 --> 01:55:23,788
- Come on!
- I'll kill you!

1183
01:55:23,789 --> 01:55:26,289
Kill me!
Get up!

1184
01:55:26,292 --> 01:55:27,926
Get out of here!

1185
01:55:27,927 --> 01:55:31,419
- I hate you!
- Now go ahead. Now I'll kill you.

1186
01:55:31,530 --> 01:55:33,531
You guinea brat, you.

1187
01:55:33,532 --> 01:55:36,032
Get out here!

1188
01:55:44,877 --> 01:55:47,812
Connie, what's the matter?
I can't hear you. What is it?

1189
01:55:48,981 --> 01:55:51,848
Honey, talk louder.
The baby's crying.

1190
01:55:51,951 --> 01:55:53,985
Santino, I can't understand.
I don't know.

1191
01:55:53,986 --> 01:55:56,054
I don't understand.

1192
01:55:56,055 --> 01:55:58,555
Yeah, Connie.

1193
01:56:03,095 --> 01:56:05,595
Listen, you wait there.

1194
01:56:07,466 --> 01:56:09,966
No, you just wait there.

1195
01:56:11,770 --> 01:56:14,671
- That son of a bitch.
- Sonny, what's the matter?

1196
01:56:14,773 --> 01:56:16,908
- Son of a bitch!
- What's the matter?

1197
01:56:16,909 --> 01:56:19,409
Damn it!

1198
01:56:21,580 --> 01:56:24,208
Open the goddamn gate.
Get off your ass.

1199
01:56:40,733 --> 01:56:43,566
- Sonny, come on!
- Get out of here!

1200
01:56:43,669 --> 01:56:46,169
Go after him.
Go on.

1201
01:57:14,566 --> 01:57:16,501
Son of a bitch.

1202
01:57:16,502 --> 01:57:19,002
Come on! Come on!

1203
01:59:06,078 --> 01:59:08,578
Give me a drop.

1204
01:59:16,188 --> 01:59:18,688
My wife is crying upstairs.

1205
01:59:20,859 --> 01:59:23,359
I hear cars coming to the house.

1206
01:59:27,933 --> 01:59:30,433
Consigliere of mine...

1207
01:59:31,303 --> 01:59:34,238
I think you should tell your Don
what everyone seems to know.

1208
01:59:34,339 --> 01:59:36,839
Well, I didn't tell Mama anything.

1209
01:59:38,043 --> 01:59:41,570
I was about to come up and wake you
just now and tell you.

1210
01:59:44,716 --> 01:59:47,216
But you needed a drink first.

1211
01:59:53,792 --> 01:59:56,292
Now you've had your drink.

1212
02:00:01,834 --> 02:00:05,998
They shot Sonny on the causeway.
He's dead.

1213
02:00:23,288 --> 02:00:25,788
I want all inquiries made.

1214
02:00:29,962 --> 02:00:32,462
I want no acts of vengeance.

1215
02:00:33,999 --> 02:00:36,499
I want you to arrange a meeting...

1216
02:00:37,803 --> 02:00:40,303
with the heads
of the five families.

1217
02:00:42,541 --> 02:00:45,041
This war stops now.

1218
02:01:06,498 --> 02:01:09,023
Call Bonasera.

1219
02:01:09,134 --> 02:01:11,634
We need him now.

1220
02:01:23,482 --> 02:01:26,451
This is Tom Hagen
calling for Vito Corleone...

1221
02:01:26,552 --> 02:01:28,653
at his request.

1222
02:01:28,654 --> 02:01:30,955
Now, you owe your Don a service.

1223
02:01:30,956 --> 02:01:34,790
<i>He has no doubt that
you will repay it.</i>

1224
02:01:34,893 --> 02:01:37,657
<i>Now, he will be at your
funeral parlor in one hour.</i>

1225
02:01:37,763 --> 02:01:40,263
<i>Be there to greet him.</i>

1226
02:02:00,485 --> 02:02:02,820
Well, my friend...

1227
02:02:02,821 --> 02:02:05,289
are you ready
to do me this service?

1228
02:02:05,290 --> 02:02:06,958
Yes.

1229
02:02:06,959 --> 02:02:09,484
What do you want me to do?

1230
02:02:16,835 --> 02:02:19,861
I want you to use
all your powers...

1231
02:02:19,972 --> 02:02:22,472
and all your skills.

1232
02:02:25,477 --> 02:02:27,977
I don't want his mother
to see him this way.

1233
02:02:44,529 --> 02:02:47,029
Look how they massacred my boy.

1234
02:03:21,900 --> 02:03:23,801
Monday, Tuesday, Thursday...

1235
02:03:23,802 --> 02:03:26,430
Wednesday, Friday,
Sunday, Saturday.

1236
02:04:58,830 --> 02:05:01,330
- Fabrizio.
- Yes, sir?

1237
02:05:02,467 --> 02:05:04,135
Are you driving yourself, boss?

1238
02:05:04,136 --> 02:05:06,437
- Yes.
- Is your wife coming with you?

1239
02:05:06,438 --> 02:05:09,999
No. I want you to take her to her father's
house till I know things are safe.

1240
02:05:10,108 --> 02:05:12,608
Okay. Anything you say, boss.

1241
02:06:21,646 --> 02:06:23,581
Don Barzini,
I want to thank you...

1242
02:06:23,582 --> 02:06:27,109
for helping me organize
this meeting here today.

1243
02:06:27,219 --> 02:06:30,586
And also the other heads
of the five families...

1244
02:06:30,689 --> 02:06:33,189
from New York and New Jersey.

1245
02:06:34,192 --> 02:06:37,218
Carmine Cuneo from the Bronx.

1246
02:06:39,698 --> 02:06:42,198
From Brooklyn...

1247
02:06:42,367 --> 02:06:44,867
Philip Tattaglia.

1248
02:06:46,271 --> 02:06:49,104
And from Staten Island...

1249
02:06:49,207 --> 02:06:52,472
we have with us Victor Strachi.

1250
02:06:52,577 --> 02:06:55,077
And all the other associates
that came as far...

1251
02:06:55,146 --> 02:06:58,274
as from California
and Kansas City...

1252
02:06:58,383 --> 02:07:00,818
and all the other territories
of the country.

1253
02:07:00,819 --> 02:07:03,319
Thank you.

1254
02:07:08,927 --> 02:07:11,427
How did things ever get so far?

1255
02:07:12,464 --> 02:07:14,964
I don't know.

1256
02:07:16,201 --> 02:07:19,693
It was so unfortunate
and so unnecessary.

1257
02:07:22,774 --> 02:07:25,009
Tattaglia lost a son...

1258
02:07:25,010 --> 02:07:27,510
and I lost a son.

1259
02:07:28,246 --> 02:07:31,841
We're quits,
and if Tattaglia agrees...

1260
02:07:31,950 --> 02:07:36,011
then I'm willing to let things
go on the way they were before.

1261
02:07:37,656 --> 02:07:41,183
We are all grateful to Don Corleone
for calling this meeting.

1262
02:07:41,293 --> 02:07:43,989
We all know him
as a man of his word.

1263
02:07:44,095 --> 02:07:46,330
A modest man.
He'll always listen to reason.

1264
02:07:46,331 --> 02:07:48,831
Yes, Don Barzini.

1265
02:07:48,867 --> 02:07:50,935
He's too modest.

1266
02:07:50,936 --> 02:07:53,905
He had all the judges
and politicians in his pocket.

1267
02:07:55,307 --> 02:07:58,140
He refused to share them.

1268
02:07:58,243 --> 02:08:01,235
When did I ever refuse
an accommodation?

1269
02:08:02,113 --> 02:08:04,613
All of you know me here.

1270
02:08:05,483 --> 02:08:09,510
When did I ever refuse,
except one time?

1271
02:08:09,621 --> 02:08:12,121
And why?

1272
02:08:12,290 --> 02:08:14,790
Because I believe
this drug business...

1273
02:08:14,893 --> 02:08:18,021
is going to destroy us
in the years to come.

1274
02:08:18,129 --> 02:08:21,860
I mean, it's not like gambling
or liquor or even women...

1275
02:08:21,967 --> 02:08:24,697
which is something that
most people want nowadays...

1276
02:08:24,803 --> 02:08:28,261
and is forbidden to them by
the pezzonovante of the church.

1277
02:08:28,373 --> 02:08:31,467
Even the police departments
that have helped us in the past...

1278
02:08:31,576 --> 02:08:33,410
with gambling and other things...

1279
02:08:33,411 --> 02:08:37,541
are gonna refuse to help us
when it comes to narcotics.

1280
02:08:37,649 --> 02:08:40,584
And I believed that then...

1281
02:08:40,685 --> 02:08:42,820
and I believe that now.

1282
02:08:42,821 --> 02:08:45,122
Times have changed.

1283
02:08:45,123 --> 02:08:47,391
It's not like the old days...

1284
02:08:47,392 --> 02:08:49,892
when we could do
anything we want.

1285
02:08:49,928 --> 02:08:52,829
A refusal is not the act of a friend.

1286
02:08:52,931 --> 02:08:56,867
If Don Corleone had all the judges
and the politicians in New York...

1287
02:08:56,968 --> 02:08:59,960
then he must share them
or let others use them.

1288
02:09:00,071 --> 02:09:03,234
He must let us draw
the water from the well.

1289
02:09:04,175 --> 02:09:07,736
Certainly, he can present a bill
for such services.

1290
02:09:07,846 --> 02:09:10,576
After all, we are not Communists.

1291
02:09:13,551 --> 02:09:16,611
I also don't believe in drugs.

1292
02:09:16,721 --> 02:09:18,956
For years,
I paid my people extra...

1293
02:09:18,957 --> 02:09:21,358
so they wouldn't do
that kind of business.

1294
02:09:21,359 --> 02:09:24,795
Somebody comes to them and says,
"I have powders.

1295
02:09:24,896 --> 02:09:27,626
If you put up a three, four
thousand dollar investment,

1296
02:09:28,600 --> 02:09:31,262
we can make 50,000 distributing."

1297
02:09:32,370 --> 02:09:36,170
So they can't resist. I want
to control it as a business...

1298
02:09:36,274 --> 02:09:38,742
to keep it respectable.

1299
02:09:38,743 --> 02:09:43,271
I don't want it near schools.
I don't want it sold to children.

1300
02:09:43,381 --> 02:09:45,881
That's an infamia.

1301
02:09:46,418 --> 02:09:50,354
In my city, we would keep the traffic
in the dark people, the colored.

1302
02:09:50,455 --> 02:09:53,322
They're animals anyway,
so let them lose their souls.

1303
02:10:00,298 --> 02:10:03,597
I hoped that we could come here
and reason together.

1304
02:10:05,336 --> 02:10:08,499
And as a reasonable man, I'm willing
to do whatever's necessary...

1305
02:10:08,606 --> 02:10:12,098
to find a peaceful solution
to these problems.

1306
02:10:12,210 --> 02:10:14,378
Then we are agreed.

1307
02:10:14,379 --> 02:10:16,814
The traffic in drugs
will be permitted, but controlled.

1308
02:10:16,815 --> 02:10:19,375
And Don Corleone will give our
protection in the east...

1309
02:10:19,484 --> 02:10:21,418
and there will be the peace.

1310
02:10:21,419 --> 02:10:25,287
But I must have strict assurance
from Corleone.

1311
02:10:25,390 --> 02:10:28,553
As time goes by and
his position becomes stronger...

1312
02:10:28,660 --> 02:10:31,185
will he attempt
any individual vendetta?

1313
02:10:31,296 --> 02:10:33,363
Look, we are all
reasonable men here.

1314
02:10:33,364 --> 02:10:36,800
We don't have to give assurances
as if we were lawyers.

1315
02:10:36,901 --> 02:10:39,136
You talk about vengeance.

1316
02:10:39,137 --> 02:10:42,402
Is vengeance gonna bring
your son back to you?

1317
02:10:42,507 --> 02:10:45,007
Or my boy to me?

1318
02:10:45,677 --> 02:10:48,177
I forego the vengeance of my son.

1319
02:10:51,316 --> 02:10:53,816
But I have selfish reasons.

1320
02:10:55,820 --> 02:10:57,855
My youngest son...

1321
02:10:57,856 --> 02:11:00,356
was forced to leave this country...

1322
02:11:01,359 --> 02:11:03,859
because of this Sollozzo business.

1323
02:11:04,329 --> 02:11:07,162
All right.
And I have to make arrangements...

1324
02:11:07,265 --> 02:11:11,895
to bring him back here safely,
cleared of all these false charges.

1325
02:11:13,538 --> 02:11:16,564
But I'm a superstitious man.

1326
02:11:16,674 --> 02:11:19,234
And if some unlucky accident
should befall him...

1327
02:11:19,344 --> 02:11:23,075
if he should get shot
in the head by a police officer...

1328
02:11:23,181 --> 02:11:27,015
or if he should hang himself
in his jail cell...

1329
02:11:27,118 --> 02:11:29,618
of if he's struck
by a bolt of lightening...

1330
02:11:31,256 --> 02:11:34,282
then I'm going to blame
some of the people in this room.

1331
02:11:36,494 --> 02:11:38,994
And that I do not forgive.

1332
02:11:41,332 --> 02:11:43,832
But that aside...

1333
02:11:46,771 --> 02:11:49,271
let me say that I swear...

1334
02:11:50,708 --> 02:11:53,802
on the souls of my grandchildren...

1335
02:11:53,912 --> 02:11:57,439
that I will not be the one to break
the peace we've made here today.

1336
02:12:23,841 --> 02:12:25,842
When I meet with the Tattaglia
people, should I insist...

1337
02:12:25,843 --> 02:12:29,210
that all these drug middlemen
have clean records?

1338
02:12:29,314 --> 02:12:31,814
Mention it.
Don't insist.

1339
02:12:33,651 --> 02:12:36,151
Barzini is a man who'll know that
without being told.

1340
02:12:37,488 --> 02:12:40,082
You mean Tattaglia.

1341
02:12:40,191 --> 02:12:42,921
Tattaglia's a pimp.

1342
02:12:43,027 --> 02:12:45,527
He never could've outfought Santino.

1343
02:12:48,866 --> 02:12:52,529
But I didn't know until this day
that it was...

1344
02:12:52,637 --> 02:12:55,137
Barzini all along.

1345
02:13:09,787 --> 02:13:12,287
Come on, Nancy.

1346
02:13:12,991 --> 02:13:15,491
Keep together, everyone.
Brian?

1347
02:13:16,861 --> 02:13:19,361
Okay. All right.

1348
02:13:31,909 --> 02:13:34,434
How long have you been back?

1349
02:13:34,545 --> 02:13:37,045
I've been back a year.

1350
02:13:37,982 --> 02:13:40,507
Longer than that, I think.

1351
02:13:42,754 --> 02:13:45,254
It's good to see you, Kay.

1352
02:13:51,162 --> 02:13:53,662
Hi, Miss Adams!

1353
02:13:56,000 --> 02:13:58,500
I'm working for my father now, Kay.

1354
02:14:01,139 --> 02:14:03,173
He's been sick.

1355
02:14:03,174 --> 02:14:05,609
Very sick.

1356
02:14:05,610 --> 02:14:07,711
But you're not like him, Michael.

1357
02:14:07,712 --> 02:14:10,237
I thought you weren't going
to become a man like your father.

1358
02:14:10,348 --> 02:14:12,848
That's what you told me.

1359
02:14:13,384 --> 02:14:16,114
My father's no different
than any other powerful man.

1360
02:14:17,789 --> 02:14:21,350
Any man who's responsible
for other people.

1361
02:14:22,460 --> 02:14:24,960
Like a senator or a president.

1362
02:14:24,962 --> 02:14:27,487
- Do you know how naive you sound?
- Why?

1363
02:14:27,598 --> 02:14:30,192
Senators and presidents
don't have men killed.

1364
02:14:31,537 --> 02:14:32,537
Oh.

1365
02:14:33,538 --> 02:14:36,038
Who's being naive, Kay?

1366
02:14:36,674 --> 02:14:38,909
Kay, my father's way
of doing things is over.

1367
02:14:38,910 --> 02:14:42,402
It's finished.
Even he knows that.

1368
02:14:42,513 --> 02:14:44,548
I mean, in five years
the Corleone family...

1369
02:14:44,549 --> 02:14:47,049
is going to be completely legitimate.

1370
02:14:48,820 --> 02:14:51,687
Trust me. That's all I can tell you
about my business.

1371
02:14:51,688 --> 02:14:52,688
Kay.

1372
02:14:54,158 --> 02:14:56,526
Michael, why did you come here?

1373
02:14:56,527 --> 02:14:58,729
Why?

1374
02:14:58,730 --> 02:15:00,797
What do you want with me
after all this time...

1375
02:15:00,798 --> 02:15:03,323
without even calling or writing?

1376
02:15:03,434 --> 02:15:05,435
I came here because I need you.

1377
02:15:05,436 --> 02:15:07,961
- Because I care for you.
- Please stop it, Michael.

1378
02:15:08,072 --> 02:15:11,200
Because I want you to marry me.

1379
02:15:12,710 --> 02:15:15,210
- It's too late. It's too late.
- Please. Kay.

1380
02:15:16,914 --> 02:15:20,782
I'll do anything you ask, anything to
make up for what's happened to us.

1381
02:15:22,587 --> 02:15:24,921
Because that's important, Kay.

1382
02:15:24,922 --> 02:15:28,414
Because what's important is that...

1383
02:15:28,526 --> 02:15:30,360
we have each other.

1384
02:15:30,361 --> 02:15:33,262
That we have a life together.

1385
02:15:33,364 --> 02:15:36,822
That we have children.
Our children.

1386
02:15:37,323 --> 02:15:38,323
Kay...

1387
02:15:38,970 --> 02:15:41,700
I need you...

1388
02:15:41,806 --> 02:15:44,306
and I love you.

1389
02:16:05,430 --> 02:16:07,431
Barzini's people
chisel my territory...

1390
02:16:07,432 --> 02:16:09,299
and we do nothing about it.

1391
02:16:09,300 --> 02:16:11,981
Pretty soon, there won't be one place
in Brooklyn I can hang my hat.

1392
02:16:12,036 --> 02:16:14,561
- Just be patient.
- I'm not askin' you for help, Mike.

1393
02:16:14,672 --> 02:16:17,197
- Just take off the handcuffs.
- Be patient.

1394
02:16:17,308 --> 02:16:19,443
We gotta protect ourselves.

1395
02:16:19,444 --> 02:16:21,445
Give me a chance to recruit
some new men.

1396
02:16:21,446 --> 02:16:23,079
No.

1397
02:16:23,080 --> 02:16:25,580
I don't wanna give Barzini
an excuse to start fighting.

1398
02:16:25,650 --> 02:16:28,175
Mike, you're wrong.

1399
02:16:28,286 --> 02:16:31,915
Don Corleone, you once said
that the day would come...

1400
02:16:32,023 --> 02:16:34,719
when Tessio and me
could form our own family.

1401
02:16:34,826 --> 02:16:36,827
Till today,
I would never think of it.

1402
02:16:36,828 --> 02:16:39,196
I must ask your permission.

1403
02:16:39,197 --> 02:16:42,428
Well, Michael is now
head of the family...

1404
02:16:42,533 --> 02:16:45,229
and if he gives his permission,
then you have my blessing.

1405
02:16:46,804 --> 02:16:49,304
After we make the move to Nevada...

1406
02:16:49,407 --> 02:16:52,399
you can break off from the Corleone
family and go on your own.

1407
02:16:52,510 --> 02:16:55,308
- After we make the move to Nevada.
- How long will that be?

1408
02:16:56,547 --> 02:16:58,181
Six months.

1409
02:16:58,182 --> 02:17:01,640
Forgive me, Godfather,
but with you gone...

1410
02:17:01,752 --> 02:17:04,721
me and Pete'll come under
Barzini's thumb sooner or later.

1411
02:17:04,822 --> 02:17:07,322
And I hate that goddamn Barzini.

1412
02:17:07,358 --> 02:17:10,293
In six months' time, there won't be
nothing left to build on.

1413
02:17:10,394 --> 02:17:13,386
- You have faith in my judgment?
- Yes.

1414
02:17:13,498 --> 02:17:16,296
- Do I have your loyalty?
- Yes, always, Godfather.

1415
02:17:16,400 --> 02:17:18,668
Then be a friend to Michael...

1416
02:17:18,669 --> 02:17:21,169
and do as he says.

1417
02:17:24,609 --> 02:17:26,810
There are things being negotiated
now that are going to solve...

1418
02:17:26,811 --> 02:17:29,905
all your problems
and answer all your questions.

1419
02:17:30,014 --> 02:17:32,514
That's all I can tell you now.

1420
02:17:33,017 --> 02:17:35,645
Carlo, you grew up in Nevada.

1421
02:17:35,753 --> 02:17:38,916
When we make our move there,
you're gonna be my right-hand man.

1422
02:17:39,023 --> 02:17:41,719
Tom Hagen's no longer consigliere.

1423
02:17:41,826 --> 02:17:44,326
He's gonna be our lawyer in Vegas.

1424
02:17:44,328 --> 02:17:46,796
That's no reflection on Tom,
but that's the way I want it.

1425
02:17:46,797 --> 02:17:48,732
Besides, if I ever need help...

1426
02:17:48,733 --> 02:17:51,034
who's a better consigliere
than my father?

1427
02:17:51,035 --> 02:17:53,535
Now that's it.

1428
02:18:11,622 --> 02:18:14,122
- Thank you, Papa.
- I'm happy for you, Carlo.

1429
02:18:15,528 --> 02:18:19,758
Mike, ehh...
Why am I out?

1430
02:18:19,864 --> 02:18:22,364
You're not a wartime consigliere, Tom.

1431
02:18:23,935 --> 02:18:26,435
Things may get rough
with the move we're trying.

1432
02:18:27,136 --> 02:18:28,136
Tom...

1433
02:18:33,711 --> 02:18:35,979
I advised Michael.

1434
02:18:35,980 --> 02:18:38,881
I never thought
you were a bad consigliere.

1435
02:18:38,983 --> 02:18:42,248
I thought Santino was a bad Don...

1436
02:18:42,353 --> 02:18:44,621
rest in peace.

1437
02:18:44,622 --> 02:18:47,648
Michael has all my confidence,
as, as you do.

1438
02:18:48,859 --> 02:18:52,386
But there are reasons why
you must have no part...

1439
02:18:52,496 --> 02:18:54,731
in what is going to happen.

1440
02:18:54,732 --> 02:18:56,232
Maybe I could help.

1441
02:18:56,233 --> 02:18:58,733
You're out, Tom.

1442
02:19:47,151 --> 02:19:49,676
I can't get over the way
your face looks.

1443
02:19:49,787 --> 02:19:52,950
It really looks good.
This doctor did some job.

1444
02:19:53,057 --> 02:19:55,685
Who talked you into it, Kay?
Hey, hey, wait.

1445
02:19:55,793 --> 02:19:58,194
Leave them out here.
We'll deal with them later.

1446
02:19:58,195 --> 02:20:00,196
He's tired.
He wants to clean up.

1447
02:20:00,197 --> 02:20:03,257
For right now, let me open the door.
All right?

1448
02:20:08,806 --> 02:20:11,141
Hello, Mike.
Welcome to Las Vegas.

1449
02:20:11,142 --> 02:20:14,407
All for you, kid.
It was all his idea, right?

1450
02:20:14,512 --> 02:20:17,310
- Well, your brother, Freddy...
- It was... Girls?

1451
02:20:21,052 --> 02:20:23,850
I'll be right back.
You keep them occupied.

1452
02:20:23,954 --> 02:20:26,889
That a boy.
Anything you want, kid, anything. Huh?

1453
02:20:26,991 --> 02:20:29,491
Who are the girls?

1454
02:20:30,061 --> 02:20:32,062
That's for you to find out.

1455
02:20:32,063 --> 02:20:34,930
Get rid of them, Fredo.

1456
02:20:35,032 --> 02:20:37,167
- Hey, Mike...
- Fredo, I'm here on business.

1457
02:20:37,168 --> 02:20:40,899
I leave tomorrow.
Now, get rid of them. I'm tired.

1458
02:20:41,005 --> 02:20:43,505
Get rid of the band too.

1459
02:20:48,479 --> 02:20:51,277
Hey, just take off.
Come on. Let's go.

1460
02:20:51,382 --> 02:20:54,647
Hey, that's it.
Hey, Angelo, that's it.

1461
02:20:54,752 --> 02:20:56,786
Let's go.
Hey, come on!

1462
02:20:56,787 --> 02:20:59,287
Scram!

1463
02:20:59,557 --> 02:21:01,925
Come on, honey. Let's go.
I don't know, Johnny.

1464
02:21:01,926 --> 02:21:04,094
I don't know what the hell's
the matter with him. I'm sorry.

1465
02:21:04,095 --> 02:21:06,396
It's all right, Freddy.

1466
02:21:06,397 --> 02:21:08,897
I don't know.
He's tired, he's hot.

1467
02:21:15,906 --> 02:21:18,406
What happened to Moe Greene?

1468
02:21:19,009 --> 02:21:21,509
He said he had some business.
He said give him a call...

1469
02:21:21,512 --> 02:21:23,480
when the party started.

1470
02:21:23,481 --> 02:21:25,981
Well, give him a call.

1471
02:21:26,784 --> 02:21:29,878
- Johnny, how are you?
- Hello, Mike. Nice to see you again.

1472
02:21:29,987 --> 02:21:32,155
- We're all proud of you.
- Thanks, Mike.

1473
02:21:32,156 --> 02:21:34,557
Sit down, Johnny.
I want to talk to you.

1474
02:21:34,558 --> 02:21:38,995
- The Don's proud of you, too, Johnny.
- Well, I, owe it all to him.

1475
02:21:39,096 --> 02:21:41,131
Well, he knows
how grateful you are.

1476
02:21:41,132 --> 02:21:44,192
That's why he'd like to ask
a favor of you.

1477
02:21:44,301 --> 02:21:46,801
Mike, what can I do?

1478
02:21:47,605 --> 02:21:50,165
The Corleone family is thinking
of giving up all its interests...

1479
02:21:50,174 --> 02:21:53,575
in the olive oil business,
settling out here.

1480
02:21:53,677 --> 02:21:56,942
Now, Moe Greene will sell us his
share of the casino and the hotel...

1481
02:21:57,047 --> 02:21:59,641
so it can be completely owned
by the family. Tom?

1482
02:21:59,750 --> 02:22:02,051
Hey, Mike, are you sure about that?

1483
02:22:02,052 --> 02:22:04,919
Moe loves the business. He never
said nothin' to me about sellin'.

1484
02:22:05,022 --> 02:22:07,522
Well, I'll make him an offer
he can't refuse.

1485
02:22:09,260 --> 02:22:11,694
See, Johnny...

1486
02:22:11,695 --> 02:22:13,997
see, we figure that entertainment
will be a big factor...

1487
02:22:13,998 --> 02:22:15,799
in drawing gamblers to the casino.

1488
02:22:15,800 --> 02:22:19,099
Now we hope you'll sign a contract
to appear five times a year.

1489
02:22:22,606 --> 02:22:25,871
Perhaps convince some of
your friends in the movies...

1490
02:22:25,976 --> 02:22:28,476
to do the same.

1491
02:22:28,546 --> 02:22:31,046
We're counting on you.

1492
02:22:32,650 --> 02:22:35,175
Sure, Mike.
I'll do anything for my godfather.

1493
02:22:35,286 --> 02:22:36,619
You know that.

1494
02:22:36,620 --> 02:22:39,120
Good.

1495
02:22:39,256 --> 02:22:41,491
Hey, Mike.
Hello, fellas.

1496
02:22:41,492 --> 02:22:45,189
Everybody's here. Freddy, Tom.
Good to see you, Mike.

1497
02:22:45,296 --> 02:22:47,330
- How are you, Moe?
- You got everything you want?

1498
02:22:47,331 --> 02:22:50,027
The chef cooked for you special, the
dancers will kick your tongue out...

1499
02:22:50,134 --> 02:22:51,901
and your credit is good.

1500
02:22:51,902 --> 02:22:54,543
Draw chips for everybody in the room
so they can play on the house.

1501
02:22:58,108 --> 02:23:00,608
My credit good enough
to buy you out?

1502
02:23:02,580 --> 02:23:04,514
Buy me out?

1503
02:23:04,515 --> 02:23:07,177
The casino. The hotel.

1504
02:23:07,284 --> 02:23:10,048
The Corleone family
wants to buy you out.

1505
02:23:10,154 --> 02:23:13,021
The Corleone family
wants to buy me out?

1506
02:23:13,123 --> 02:23:15,623
No, I buy you out.
You don't buy me out.

1507
02:23:15,659 --> 02:23:18,924
Your casino loses money.
Maybe we can do better.

1508
02:23:19,029 --> 02:23:21,529
You think I'm skimming
off the top, Mike?

1509
02:23:22,333 --> 02:23:24,833
You're unlucky.

1510
02:23:28,005 --> 02:23:30,473
You goddamn guineas
really make me laugh.

1511
02:23:30,474 --> 02:23:33,307
I do you a favor and take Freddy in
when you're having a bad time.

1512
02:23:33,410 --> 02:23:35,879
- And then you try to push me out!
- Wait a minute.

1513
02:23:35,880 --> 02:23:38,474
You took Freddy in because
the Corleone family...

1514
02:23:38,582 --> 02:23:41,082
bankrolled your casino,
because the Molinari family...

1515
02:23:41,185 --> 02:23:43,319
on the coast guaranteed his safety.

1516
02:23:43,320 --> 02:23:45,388
Now, we're talkin' business.
Let's talk business.

1517
02:23:45,389 --> 02:23:48,119
Yeah, let's talk business, Mike.
First of all, you're all done.

1518
02:23:48,225 --> 02:23:50,693
The Corleone family don't even have
that kind of muscle anymore.

1519
02:23:50,694 --> 02:23:53,194
The Godfather's sick, right? You're
getting chased out of New York...

1520
02:23:53,230 --> 02:23:55,031
by Barzini and the other families.

1521
02:23:55,032 --> 02:23:58,934
What do you think is going on here? You think
you can come to my hotel and take over?

1522
02:23:59,036 --> 02:24:00,870
I talked to Barzini.

1523
02:24:00,871 --> 02:24:04,136
I can make a deal with him
and still keep my hotel.

1524
02:24:04,241 --> 02:24:06,835
Is that why you slapped
my brother around in public?

1525
02:24:07,912 --> 02:24:09,613
Oh, no, that was nothin', Mike.

1526
02:24:09,914 --> 02:24:12,474
Now, now, Moe didn't mean nothin' by that.

1527
02:24:12,583 --> 02:24:15,083
Sure he flies off the handle
once in a while...

1528
02:24:15,085 --> 02:24:17,220
but Moe and me,
we're good friends, right, Moe, huh?

1529
02:24:17,221 --> 02:24:19,088
I got a business to run.

1530
02:24:19,089 --> 02:24:21,819
I gotta kick asses sometimes
to make it run right.

1531
02:24:21,926 --> 02:24:25,919
We had a little argument, Freddy and I,
so I had to straighten him out.

1532
02:24:26,030 --> 02:24:28,624
You straightened my brother out?

1533
02:24:28,732 --> 02:24:31,232
He was banging cocktail waitresses
two at a time!

1534
02:24:31,235 --> 02:24:34,136
Players couldn't get a drink at the table.
What's wrong with you?

1535
02:24:40,177 --> 02:24:43,669
I leave for New York tomorrow.
Think about a price.

1536
02:24:43,781 --> 02:24:45,481
Son of a bitch.

1537
02:24:45,482 --> 02:24:48,508
Do you know who I am?
I'm Moe Greene.

1538
02:24:48,619 --> 02:24:51,213
I made my bones when you were
going out with cheerleaders.

1539
02:24:51,322 --> 02:24:53,822
Wait a minute, Moe.
Moe, I got an idea.

1540
02:24:54,825 --> 02:24:58,022
Tom, you're the consigliere.
Now, you can talk to the Don.

1541
02:24:58,128 --> 02:25:00,129
- You can explain...
- Just a minute.

1542
02:25:00,130 --> 02:25:03,725
The Don is semiretired and Mike is
in charge of the family business now.

1543
02:25:03,834 --> 02:25:06,394
If you have anything to say,
say it to Michael.

1544
02:25:11,276 --> 02:25:15,871
Mike! You don't come to Las Vegas and
talk to a man like Moe Greene like that!

1545
02:25:18,217 --> 02:25:22,947
Fredo. You're my older brother,
and I love you.

1546
02:25:24,455 --> 02:25:26,522
But don't ever take sides
with anyone...

1547
02:25:26,523 --> 02:25:29,424
against the family again...

1548
02:25:29,526 --> 02:25:32,026
ever.

1549
02:25:38,836 --> 02:25:41,004
I have to see my father
and his people.

1550
02:25:41,005 --> 02:25:43,505
- So have dinner without me.
- Oh, Michael.

1551
02:25:45,009 --> 02:25:47,276
This weekend we'll go out.
We'll go to the city.

1552
02:25:47,277 --> 02:25:49,777
We'll see a show and we'll have dinner.
I promise.

1553
02:25:57,221 --> 02:26:00,122
Oh, Michael. Michael, your sister wants
to ask you something.

1554
02:26:00,224 --> 02:26:02,358
- Well, let her ask.
- No, she's afraid to.

1555
02:26:02,359 --> 02:26:05,590
Connie and Carlo want you to be
godfather to their little boy.

1556
02:26:05,696 --> 02:26:07,563
- Oh, we'll see.
- Will you?

1557
02:26:07,564 --> 02:26:10,064
Let me think about it. We'll see.
Come on.

1558
02:26:16,673 --> 02:26:18,608
So...

1559
02:26:18,609 --> 02:26:21,578
Barzini will move against you first.

1560
02:26:21,678 --> 02:26:26,012
He'll set up a meeting with
someone that you absolutely trust...

1561
02:26:26,116 --> 02:26:28,616
guaranteeing your safety.

1562
02:26:29,453 --> 02:26:32,718
And at that meeting,
you'll be assassinated.

1563
02:26:37,361 --> 02:26:40,558
I like to drink wine
more than I used to.

1564
02:26:41,732 --> 02:26:43,900
Anyway, I'm drinking more.

1565
02:26:43,901 --> 02:26:46,401
It's good for you, Pop.

1566
02:26:50,340 --> 02:26:52,840
I don't know.

1567
02:26:53,744 --> 02:26:56,244
Your wife and children,
are you happy with them?

1568
02:26:57,648 --> 02:26:59,715
Very happy.

1569
02:26:59,716 --> 02:27:02,241
That's good.

1570
02:27:02,352 --> 02:27:04,620
I hope you don't mind
the way I...

1571
02:27:04,621 --> 02:27:07,215
I keep going over
this Barzini business.

1572
02:27:07,324 --> 02:27:09,392
No, not at all.

1573
02:27:09,393 --> 02:27:11,761
It's an old habit.

1574
02:27:11,762 --> 02:27:14,526
I spent my life
tryin' not to be careless.

1575
02:27:16,400 --> 02:27:19,233
Women and children can be careless,
but not men.

1576
02:27:23,107 --> 02:27:25,667
- How's your boy?
- He's good.

1577
02:27:25,776 --> 02:27:28,276
You know, he looks
more like you every day.

1578
02:27:31,081 --> 02:27:33,349
He's smarter than I am.

1579
02:27:33,350 --> 02:27:35,850
Three years old,
he can read the funny papers.

1580
02:27:37,654 --> 02:27:40,154
Reads the funny papers.

1581
02:27:46,897 --> 02:27:49,397
I want you to arrange
to have a telephone man...

1582
02:27:49,399 --> 02:27:52,527
check all the calls that go
in and out of here.

1583
02:27:52,636 --> 02:27:54,770
- I did it already, Pop.
- Could be anyone.

1584
02:27:54,771 --> 02:27:58,298
- Pop, I took care of that.
- Oh, that's right. I forgot.

1585
02:28:02,012 --> 02:28:04,413
What's the matter?

1586
02:28:04,414 --> 02:28:06,914
What's bothering you?

1587
02:28:09,686 --> 02:28:12,186
I'll handle it.

1588
02:28:12,589 --> 02:28:15,089
I told you I can handle it,
I'll handle it.

1589
02:28:28,138 --> 02:28:32,472
I knew that Santino was gonna
have to go through all this...

1590
02:28:32,576 --> 02:28:34,477
and Fredo...

1591
02:28:34,478 --> 02:28:36,946
Well...

1592
02:28:36,947 --> 02:28:39,447
Fredo was...

1593
02:28:40,984 --> 02:28:43,748
But I never, I never wanted this for you.

1594
02:28:46,023 --> 02:28:48,856
I worked my whole life...
I don't apologize...

1595
02:28:48,959 --> 02:28:51,127
to take care of my family...

1596
02:28:51,128 --> 02:28:54,996
and I refused to be a fool...

1597
02:28:55,098 --> 02:28:59,159
dancing on a string
held by all those big shots.

1598
02:29:01,271 --> 02:29:04,434
I don't apologize. That's my life.
But I thought that...

1599
02:29:06,410 --> 02:29:09,004
that when it was your time...

1600
02:29:09,112 --> 02:29:11,612
that you would be the one
to hold the strings.

1601
02:29:13,450 --> 02:29:15,950
Senator Corleone.

1602
02:29:16,920 --> 02:29:19,088
Governor Corleone.
Something.

1603
02:29:19,089 --> 02:29:21,589
Another pezzonovante.

1604
02:29:27,097 --> 02:29:30,931
Just wasn't enough time, Michael.
Wasn't enough time.

1605
02:29:31,034 --> 02:29:33,628
We'll get there, Pop.

1606
02:29:33,737 --> 02:29:36,237
We'll get there.

1607
02:29:39,476 --> 02:29:43,845
Now listen. Whoever comes to you
with this Barzini meeting...

1608
02:29:43,947 --> 02:29:45,715
he's the traitor.

1609
02:29:45,716 --> 02:29:48,216
Don't forget that.

1610
02:30:03,967 --> 02:30:06,467
Put it over the tree.

1611
02:30:21,251 --> 02:30:23,719
- Can I water these?
- Yeah.

1612
02:30:23,720 --> 02:30:25,288
That's fine.

1613
02:30:25,289 --> 02:30:27,789
Over here.
Over here.

1614
02:30:29,893 --> 02:30:32,393
Be careful.
You're spilling it.

1615
02:30:38,702 --> 02:30:41,202
Anthony, come here.

1616
02:30:46,610 --> 02:30:49,110
Go ahead. That's right.
We'll put it right there.

1617
02:30:54,918 --> 02:30:57,418
I'll show you something.
Come here.

1618
02:30:59,923 --> 02:31:02,423
Now, you stand there.

1619
02:31:05,529 --> 02:31:08,029
Give me an orange!

1620
02:31:25,615 --> 02:31:28,115
That's a new trick.

1621
02:31:28,685 --> 02:31:31,245
You run in there.
Run in there.

1622
02:31:43,867 --> 02:31:46,367
- Where are you?
- Who?

1623
02:32:19,503 --> 02:32:22,003
Ouch!

1624
02:34:43,547 --> 02:34:46,047
Mike, can I have a minute?

1625
02:34:56,393 --> 02:34:58,861
Barzini wants to arrange a meeting.

1626
02:34:58,862 --> 02:35:01,362
He says we can straighten
any of our problems out.

1627
02:35:03,033 --> 02:35:05,533
- You talked to him?
- Yeah.

1628
02:35:06,469 --> 02:35:08,904
I can arrange security...

1629
02:35:08,905 --> 02:35:11,405
on my territory.

1630
02:35:13,343 --> 02:35:15,344
All right?

1631
02:35:15,345 --> 02:35:18,178
- All right.
- All right.

1632
02:35:33,463 --> 02:35:35,963
Do you know how
they're gonna come at you?

1633
02:35:38,902 --> 02:35:41,337
They're arranging a meeting
in Brooklyn.

1634
02:35:41,338 --> 02:35:43,838
Tessio's ground...

1635
02:35:44,708 --> 02:35:47,208
where I'll be safe.

1636
02:35:58,755 --> 02:36:02,350
I always thought it would've been
Clemenza, not Tessio.

1637
02:36:02,459 --> 02:36:04,827
It's the smart move.

1638
02:36:04,828 --> 02:36:07,328
Tessio was always smarter.

1639
02:36:08,531 --> 02:36:10,833
But I'm gonna wait.

1640
02:36:10,834 --> 02:36:13,334
After the baptism.

1641
02:36:15,305 --> 02:36:17,865
I've decided to be godfather
to Connie's baby.

1642
02:36:19,209 --> 02:36:22,144
And then I'll meet
with Don Barzini...

1643
02:36:22,245 --> 02:36:24,713
and Tattaglia...

1644
02:36:24,714 --> 02:36:27,214
all the heads
of the five families.

1645
02:36:53,715 --> 02:36:55,715
Go forth from him, unclean spirit,

1646
02:36:55,916 --> 02:36:59,116
and give place to the Holy Spirit,
the Spirit of God.

1647
02:37:01,117 --> 02:37:02,117
Let us pray.

1648
02:37:02,118 --> 02:37:05,118
Our prayers through through
Christ our Lord. So be it.

1649
02:37:05,719 --> 02:37:06,719
Michael.

1650
02:37:06,720 --> 02:37:09,720
Signed with the sign of the Lord's cross,

1651
02:37:10,721 --> 02:37:13,721
so that, preserving this first experience
of the greatness of thy glory,

1652
02:37:13,722 --> 02:37:16,722
he may deserve, by keeping
thy commandments,

1653
02:37:16,723 --> 02:37:19,723
<i>to attain to the glory of regeneration.</i>

1654
02:37:19,724 --> 02:37:22,724
<i>Through Christ our Lord. So be it.</i>

1655
02:37:22,725 --> 02:37:25,725
<i>Let us pray.
Almighty, everlasting God,</i>

1656
02:37:25,726 --> 02:37:28,226
<i>Father of our Lord Jesus Christ,</i>

1657
02:37:28,227 --> 02:37:31,227
<i>look graciously down upon this,
thy servant, Michael.</i>

1658
02:37:31,228 --> 02:37:34,228
Who shall come to judge the living
and the dead,

1659
02:37:34,229 --> 02:37:37,229
and the world by fire. So be it.

1660
02:37:37,230 --> 02:37:39,530
Michael. Receive the salt of wisdom.

1661
02:37:39,531 --> 02:37:41,831
Let it be to thee a token of mercy
unto everlasting life.

1662
02:37:41,832 --> 02:37:43,832
May it make your way easy to eternal life.
So be it.

1663
02:37:43,833 --> 02:37:46,333
May the almighty God, the Father
of our Lord Jesus Christ,

1664
02:37:46,334 --> 02:37:48,834
<i>Who hath regenerated thee by water
and the Holy Spirit,</i>

1665
02:37:49,835 --> 02:37:52,335
<i>and who hath given thee the
remission of all thy sins,</i>

1666
02:37:52,836 --> 02:37:56,336
<i>may he, himself anoint thee with
the Chrism of Salvation,</i>

1667
02:37:56,337 --> 02:37:59,337
<i>in the same Christ Jesus our Lord,
unto life eternal. So be it.</i>

1668
02:38:00,338 --> 02:38:03,638
I annoint you with the oil of salvation
in Christ Jesus our Lord,

1669
02:38:03,939 --> 02:38:06,939
that you may have everlasting life.
So be it.

1670
02:38:14,340 --> 02:38:17,340
<i>Do you believe in the Holy Ghost,
the Holy Catholic Church,</i>

1671
02:38:17,341 --> 02:38:20,341
<i>the communion of Saints,
the forgiveness of sins,</i>

1672
02:38:20,342 --> 02:38:23,842
<i>the resurrection of the body
and life everlasting? I do believe.</i>

1673
02:38:24,843 --> 02:38:27,843
I exorcise thee, unclean spirit,
in the name of the Father,

1674
02:38:27,844 --> 02:38:30,844
and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit,

1675
02:38:30,845 --> 02:38:34,845
that thou goest out and depart from
this servant of God, Michael.

1676
02:38:34,846 --> 02:38:38,346
For he commands thee, accursed one,

1677
02:38:40,147 --> 02:38:43,147
Be opened, for an odor of sweetness.

1678
02:38:43,148 --> 02:38:46,148
Be thou, devil, begone,

1679
02:38:46,149 --> 02:38:48,449
for the judgment of God shall draw near.

1680
02:38:48,491 --> 02:38:51,392
Michael, do you believe in God,
the Father almighty...

1681
02:38:51,494 --> 02:38:54,463
- creator of Heaven and Earth?
- I do.

1682
02:38:54,564 --> 02:38:57,863
<i>Do you believe in Jesus Christ,
his only Son, our Lord?</i>

1683
02:38:57,967 --> 02:38:59,468
<i>I do.</i>

1684
02:38:59,469 --> 02:39:03,633
<i>Do you believe in the Holy Ghost,
the Holy Catholic Church?</i>

1685
02:39:03,640 --> 02:39:04,640
<i>I do.</i>

1686
02:39:04,941 --> 02:39:08,841
<i>Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name.</i>

1687
02:39:08,842 --> 02:39:12,842
<i>Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done,
on earth as it is in heaven.</i>

1688
02:39:12,843 --> 02:39:15,643
<i>Give us this day our daily bread.</i>

1689
02:39:15,644 --> 02:39:17,644
<i>And forgive us our trespasses,</i>

1690
02:39:17,845 --> 02:39:20,938
<i>as we forgive them that
trespass against us.</i>

1691
02:39:20,939 --> 02:39:23,939
<i>And lead us not into temptation,</i>

1692
02:39:23,940 --> 02:39:25,940
<i>but deliver us from evil.
So be it.</i>

1693
02:39:25,941 --> 02:39:27,441
Michael.

1694
02:39:27,442 --> 02:39:30,442
Enter thou into the temple of God,

1695
02:39:30,443 --> 02:39:33,443
that thou mayest have part with Christ
unto life everlasting. So be it.

1696
02:39:33,444 --> 02:39:35,944
I believe in God the Father almighty,

1697
02:39:35,945 --> 02:39:37,945
Creator of heaven and earth,

1698
02:39:37,946 --> 02:39:41,446
<i>and in Jesus Christ his only
son our Lord,</i>

1699
02:39:41,447 --> 02:39:43,747
<i>who was conceived by the Holy Ghost,</i>

1700
02:39:43,748 --> 02:39:45,748
<i>born of the Virgin Mary,</i>

1701
02:39:45,749 --> 02:39:49,049
<i>suffered under Pontius Pilate,
was crucified, dead, and buried.</i>

1702
02:39:49,051 --> 02:39:51,751
<i>He descended into Hell.
On the third day,</i>

1703
02:39:51,752 --> 02:39:55,752
<i>He rose again from the dead.
He ascended into heaven,</i>

1704
02:39:55,753 --> 02:39:58,553
<i>and sitteth at the right hand of
God the Father almighty,</i>

1705
02:39:58,554 --> 02:40:01,054
<i>from thence shall he come to judge
the living and the dead.</i>

1706
02:40:01,055 --> 02:40:04,055
<i>I believe in the Holy Ghost,
the Holy Catholic Church,</i>

1707
02:40:04,056 --> 02:40:07,056
<i>the communion of saints,
the forgiveness of sins,</i>

1708
02:40:07,057 --> 02:40:09,857
<i>the resurrection of the body,
and life everlasting. So be it.</i>

1709
02:40:09,939 --> 02:40:14,876
Michael Francis Rizzi,
do you renounce Satan?

1710
02:40:21,284 --> 02:40:23,784
I do renounce him.

1711
02:40:32,095 --> 02:40:34,595
And all his works?

1712
02:40:46,809 --> 02:40:49,309
I do renounce them.

1713
02:40:54,183 --> 02:40:58,142
- And all his pomps?
- I do renounce them.

1714
02:41:13,536 --> 02:41:17,597
Michael Rizzi,
will you be baptized?

1715
02:41:17,707 --> 02:41:19,707
I will.

1716
02:41:19,708 --> 02:41:22,008
In the name of the Father,

1717
02:41:22,009 --> 02:41:24,009
<i>and of the Son,</i>

1718
02:41:24,010 --> 02:41:26,410
<i>and of the Holy Spirit.</i>

1719
02:41:26,749 --> 02:41:29,309
<i>Michael Rizzi, go in peace.</i>

1720
02:41:29,419 --> 02:41:32,445
And may the Lord be with you.
So be it.

1721
02:42:14,564 --> 02:42:16,565
- Carlo.
- What?

1722
02:42:16,566 --> 02:42:18,800
Can't go to Vegas.
Something's come up.

1723
02:42:18,801 --> 02:42:20,836
Everybody's gonna have to leave
without us.

1724
02:42:20,837 --> 02:42:23,397
- It's our first vacation together.
- Connie, please.

1725
02:42:23,506 --> 02:42:25,507
- What do you wanna do?
- Go back to the house.

1726
02:42:25,508 --> 02:42:28,375
Wait for my call.
It's important.

1727
02:42:28,478 --> 02:42:30,978
I'll only be a couple of days.

1728
02:42:33,416 --> 02:42:35,916
Have a nice trip, Mama.

1729
02:42:46,929 --> 02:42:49,429
We're on our way to Brooklyn.

1730
02:42:51,267 --> 02:42:53,668
I hope Mike can get us
a good deal tonight.

1731
02:42:53,669 --> 02:42:56,169
I'm sure he will.

1732
02:43:02,912 --> 02:43:05,938
Sal, Tom, the boss says
he'll come in a separate car.

1733
02:43:06,049 --> 02:43:08,250
He says for you two
to go on ahead.

1734
02:43:08,251 --> 02:43:10,879
Hell, he can't do that.
It screws up all my arrangements.

1735
02:43:10,987 --> 02:43:13,487
- Well that's what he said.
- I can't go either, Sal.

1736
02:43:26,102 --> 02:43:28,866
Tell Mike it was only business.

1737
02:43:28,971 --> 02:43:31,471
I always liked him.

1738
02:43:31,641 --> 02:43:34,141
- He understands that.
- Excuse me, Sal.

1739
02:43:40,550 --> 02:43:43,050
Tom, can you get me off the hook?

1740
02:43:44,153 --> 02:43:46,849
- For old times' sake.
- Can't do it, Sally.

1741
02:44:32,802 --> 02:44:35,302
You have to answer
for Santino, Carlo.

1742
02:44:40,209 --> 02:44:42,043
Mike, you got it all wrong.

1743
02:44:42,044 --> 02:44:44,544
You fingered Sonny
for the Barzini people.

1744
02:44:46,149 --> 02:44:49,209
That little farce you played
with my sister.

1745
02:44:49,318 --> 02:44:51,319
Did you think that could fool
a Corleone?

1746
02:44:51,320 --> 02:44:54,483
Mike, I'm innocent.
I swear on the kids.

1747
02:44:54,590 --> 02:44:57,090
- Please, don't do this to me.
- Sit down.

1748
02:45:00,229 --> 02:45:02,729
Don't do this to me, please.

1749
02:45:11,607 --> 02:45:14,107
Barzini's dead.

1750
02:45:15,278 --> 02:45:17,778
So is Phillip Tattaglia...

1751
02:45:18,981 --> 02:45:21,481
Moe Greene...

1752
02:45:21,484 --> 02:45:23,984
Stracci...

1753
02:45:24,554 --> 02:45:27,054
Cuneo.

1754
02:45:27,123 --> 02:45:30,615
Today I settle all family business,
so don't tell me you're innocent, Carlo.

1755
02:45:32,495 --> 02:45:34,995
Admit what you did.

1756
02:45:38,134 --> 02:45:40,634
Get him a drink.

1757
02:45:46,275 --> 02:45:48,710
Come on.

1758
02:45:48,711 --> 02:45:51,112
Don't be afraid, Carlo.

1759
02:45:51,113 --> 02:45:53,613
Come on. You think I'd make my sister
a widow?

1760
02:45:55,251 --> 02:45:57,751
I'm godfather to your son, Carlo.

1761
02:46:04,894 --> 02:46:06,228
Go ahead, drink.

1762
02:46:06,229 --> 02:46:08,729
Drink.

1763
02:46:11,801 --> 02:46:13,969
Now, Carlo, you're out
of the family business.

1764
02:46:13,970 --> 02:46:17,633
That's your punishment.
You're finished.

1765
02:46:17,740 --> 02:46:20,240
I'm putting you on a plane to Vegas.

1766
02:46:26,482 --> 02:46:29,883
I want you to stay there.
Understand?

1767
02:46:29,986 --> 02:46:32,486
Only don't tell me
you're innocent...

1768
02:46:34,056 --> 02:46:37,025
because it insults my intelligence.

1769
02:46:37,126 --> 02:46:39,626
It makes me very angry.

1770
02:46:42,531 --> 02:46:45,762
Now, who approached you?

1771
02:46:45,868 --> 02:46:48,368
Tattaglia or Barzini?

1772
02:46:55,511 --> 02:46:58,011
It was Barzini.

1773
02:47:00,449 --> 02:47:02,949
Good.

1774
02:47:09,592 --> 02:47:12,254
There's a car waiting for you
outside to take you to the airport.

1775
02:47:13,696 --> 02:47:16,196
I'll call your wife,
tell her what flight you're on.

1776
02:47:21,804 --> 02:47:24,304
- Please, can I...
- Get out of my sight.

1777
02:47:49,765 --> 02:47:52,265
Hello, Carlo.

1778
02:48:48,791 --> 02:48:51,589
Will you stop crying?
What are you trying to tell me?

1779
02:48:51,694 --> 02:48:54,492
- I'm trying to tell you you're wrong.
- Mama, please!

1780
02:49:02,907 --> 02:49:04,907
Michael! Michael!

1781
02:49:05,408 --> 02:49:07,908
Where is he?

1782
02:49:09,812 --> 02:49:14,840
Michael, you lousy bastard!
You killed my husband!

1783
02:49:14,950 --> 02:49:17,544
You waited until Papa died
so nobody could stop you...

1784
02:49:17,653 --> 02:49:19,187
and then you killed him!

1785
02:49:19,188 --> 02:49:22,316
You blamed him for Sonny.
You always did. Everybody did.

1786
02:49:22,425 --> 02:49:26,054
But you never thought about me!
You never gave a damn about me!

1787
02:49:26,162 --> 02:49:28,662
Now what am I gonna do?

1788
02:49:32,368 --> 02:49:34,868
Why do you think
he kept Carlo at the mall?

1789
02:49:34,937 --> 02:49:37,497
All the time he knew
he was gonna kill him.

1790
02:49:37,606 --> 02:49:40,700
And you stood godfather
to our baby.

1791
02:49:40,810 --> 02:49:43,144
You lousy, coldhearted bastard.

1792
02:49:43,145 --> 02:49:45,645
Want to know how many men
he had killed with Carlo?

1793
02:49:45,681 --> 02:49:47,449
Read the papers!
Read the papers!

1794
02:49:47,450 --> 02:49:49,950
That's your husband!
That's your husband!

1795
02:50:03,532 --> 02:50:06,032
Take her upstairs.

1796
02:50:06,068 --> 02:50:08,568
- Get her a doctor.
- Oh, God!

1797
02:50:28,624 --> 02:50:31,124
She's hysterical.

1798
02:50:35,064 --> 02:50:37,564
Hysterical.

1799
02:50:38,567 --> 02:50:41,067
Michael, is it true?

1800
02:50:42,505 --> 02:50:44,572
Don't ask me about my business, Kay.

1801
02:50:44,573 --> 02:50:48,065
- Is it true?
- Don't ask me about my business.

1802
02:50:48,177 --> 02:50:50,677
- No.
- Enough!

1803
02:51:09,064 --> 02:51:11,564
All right.

1804
02:51:13,369 --> 02:51:15,869
This one time.

1805
02:51:19,074 --> 02:51:21,574
This one time, I'll let you
ask me about my affairs.

1806
02:51:28,117 --> 02:51:30,617
Is it true?

1807
02:51:34,223 --> 02:51:36,723
Is it?

1808
02:51:37,024 --> 02:51:38,524
No.

1809
02:51:52,241 --> 02:51:54,642
I guess we both need a drink, huh?

1810
02:51:54,643 --> 02:51:57,143
Come on.

1811
02:52:26,709 --> 02:52:29,209
Don Corleone.